spbusinessdescription: Nedbank Group Limited, through its subsidiary, Nedbank Limited, provides various banking products and services in South Africa. It offers personal banking solutions, including savings deposits and investment accounts; home and personal loans, student loans, vehicle finance, private wealth finance solutions, overdrafts, and credit cards; and investment plans and services, financial and estate planning services, and wills and trust services, as well as professional banking, wealth advisory and investment management, non-resident and embassy banking, unit trust, offshore portfolio, investment banking, and foreign exchange services. The company also provides business banking services, such as business and tender accounts; call, fixed, and flexi deposits; loans and structured solutions; value added services; payments and receipts, documentary credits and collections, guarantees, and trade finance; card and cash solutions; treasury solutions; cash management, electronic banking, and merchant payment and support services; life, asset, income and credit protection, funeral, business cover, liability cover, revenue cover, and owners' insurance products; and commodities, equities, fixed income, and structured credit products. In addition, the company offers corporate banking services comprising aircraft, asset based, carbon, export credit, global commodity, infrastructure, energy, telecoms, leveraged, mining, oil and gas, private equity, and public sector finance; corporate lending and advances, and specialized distribution products; custodial services; corporate finance and debt advisory services; and beta solutions, as well as corporate and institutional investments. The company was formerly known as Nedcor Limited and changed its name to Nedbank Group Limited in 2005. The company was founded in 1973 and is headquartered in Sandown, South Africa. Nedbank Group Limited is a subsidiary of Old Mutual Life Assurance Company (SA) Limited.
Standard Bank Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, offers financial products and services in the Republic of South Africa and internationally.

Growthpoint Properties Limited, together with its subsidiary, Growthpoint Properties Australia, operates as a property investment company. The company invests in and leases retail, office, and industrial properties. As of June 30, 2011, its portfolio comprised 424 properties in South Africa and 37 properties in Australia. The company was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Barclays Africa Group Limited provides various financial products and services in South Africa and internationally. It offers personal and business banking, corporate and investment banking, wealth and investment management, and insurance services.

Anglo American Platinum Limited engages in the production and sale of platinum group metals. The company produces platinum, palladium, rhodium, ruthenium, iridium, and osmium, as well as nickel, copper, cobalt sulphate, sodium sulphate, chrome, and gold.
Sibanye Gold Limited operates as a precious metals mining company in South Africa, Zimbabwe, and the United States. The company operates through Gold and Platinum divisions.

African Rainbow Minerals Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates as a diversified mining and minerals company in South Africa and Papua New Guinea. The company explores for platinum group metals, nickel, copper, coal, iron ore, manganese ore, chrome ore, ferro manganese, and silica manganese, as well as gold. Its gold assets include nine underground mines, one open pit operation, and various surface sources in South Africa. The company is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Gold Fields Limited produces gold and holds gold reserves in South Africa, Ghana, Australia, and Peru. It engages in underground and surface gold and surface copper mining and related activities, including exploration, extraction, processing, and smelting.

AngloGold Ashanti Limited operates as a gold mining and exploration company. The company also produces silver, uranium oxide, copper, and sulphuric acid. Its portfolio includes 17 mines in South Africa, Continental Africa, Australasia, and the Americas.

MMI Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an insurance-based financial services company in South Africa and internationally. The company operates through Momentum Retail, Metropolitan Retail, Corporate and Public Sector, International, and Shareholder Capital segments. It provides wealth creation, risk, and savings solutions, as well as short-term insurance and open medical scheme solutions to customers in the upper retail and the small business segments; and savings, income generation, risk, and funeral products and solutions to entry-level markets. The company also offers solutions to enhance profitability and sustainability, as well as to protect asset base to medium and large corporates, affinity groups, labor unions, and public sector institutions. In addition, it provides Hello Doctor, a mobile health service that provides preventative care and gives people the ability to connect with a doctor to make informed decisions about their health and wellness; managed care and administration services under the CareCross brand; wellness and rewards programs under the Multiply brand; and structured insurance products, traditional cell captive facilities, reinsurance, and related services under the Guardrisk brand. Further, the company operates as a property development and property services company under the Eris brand. The company is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

Liberty Holdings Limited provides a range of insurance products and services to the individuals, families, and businesses in Africa. The company operates through Individual Arrangements, Group Arrangements, and Asset Management segments. It provides life protection, accident, critical illness, medical, disability, and income and policy protection insurance products, as well as funeral benefits and plans; and annuities, alternate solutions, balanced portfolios, umbrella solutions, investment products, and fund administration services. The company was founded in 1957 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa. Liberty Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Standard Bank Group Limited.

ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd manufactures and sells long and flat steel products. The company operates through Flat Steel Products, Long Steel Products, and Coke and Chemicals segments. It offers flat steel products, including hot rolled plates, hot and cold rolled coils, galvanized coils, color coils, electrogalvanized coils, and tinplate coils. The company also provides foundry products that include castings, such as air injection tubes, door bodies, fire bars, pallet cars, pallet frames, goose necks, etc. for coke ovens, direct reduction, sinter plant, and blast furnaces, as well as the hot and cold mills. In addition, it offers long steel products comprising fencing profiles, forgings, hexagon bars, hollow bars, mining bars, rails, reinforcing bars/Y bars, rounds and squares, special profiles, structural and heavy structural sections, window sections, wire rods, billets and blooms, hot-finished and cold-drawn seamless tubes, and forged products; and tubular products, which comprise hot rolled seamless line pipes and OCTG, hot rolled boiler tubes, and cold drawn precision products. Further, the company provides commercial coke for the ferro-alloy industry; processes and beneficiates metallurgical and steel by-products, including coal tar; and provides commercial-grade coking coal. It serves clients in agricultural, armament, automotive, bolt and nut, chains, construction, engineering, furniture and appliance, mining, packaging, piping, renewable energy, roofing and cladding, tubing, food and beverages, infrastructure, defense, and oil and gas industries primarily in the Republic of South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. The company was formerly known as Mittal Steel South Africa Limited and changed its name to ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd in October 2006. The company was founded in 1928 and is headquartered in Vanderbijlpark, the Republic of South Africa. ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd is a subsidiary of ArcelorMittal Holdings AG.
Nampak Limited manufactures and sells metal, glass, and plastic and paper packaging products worldwide.

Barloworld Limited distributes products that provide integrated rental, fleet management, product support, and logistics solutions in South Africa, the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, rest of Europe, and internationally.

AVI Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primarily manufactures, markets, and distributes food and FMCG products in South Africa. It operates through Entyce Beverages, Snackworks, I&J, Personal Care, and Footwear & Apparel segments. The company provides hot beverages, sweet and savoury biscuits and snacks, frozen convenience foods, out-of-home ranges, personal care products, cosmetics, shoes, accessories, and fashion apparel. It offers beverages under the Five Roses, Freshpak, House of Coffees, Frisco, Koffiehuis, Ellis Brown, Trinco, Ciro, Lavazza, and Douwe Egberts brands; biscuits and snacks under the Bakers, Provita, Willards, and Jumping Jack brands; frozen food under the I&J brand; and personal care products under the Yardley and Lentheric brands. The company also provides footwear and apparel under the Spitz, Carvela, Green Cross, Kurt Geiger, Lacoste, Tosoni, Nina Roche, Saffron Browne, and Gant brands. AVI Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.
Sasol Limited operates as an integrated chemicals and energy company. It operates through Mining, Exploration and Production International, Energy, Base Chemicals, and Performance Chemicals segments.

AECI Ltd operates as an explosives and specialty chemicals company in Africa, South East Asia, the United States, and Australia. It operates through Explosives, Specialty Chemicals, and Property segments. The Explosives segment develops, produces, and supplies commercial explosives, initiating systems, and blasting services for the mining, quarrying, and construction markets. The Specialty Chemicals segment supplies specialty chemical raw materials and related services for use across a range of customers in the manufacturing, mining, water treatment, agricultural, and general industrial sectors. The Property segment provides leasing services; and utilities and other services, such as centralized generation and distribution of steam, security services, potable water, electricity, effluent handling, and a rail network, as well as manages properties. The company also offers water treatment solutions, agrochemicals, and juice-based products and ingredients. AECI Ltd was founded in 1924 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Tongaat Hulett Limited, an agriculture and agri-processing business, engages in land management, property development, and agriculture activities primarily in Zimbabwe, Swaziland, Mozambique, South Africa, and internationally. It produces and sells various refined carbohydrate products from sugarcane and maize; sweeteners; energy and supplementary feeds to the livestock farming community under the Voermol brand, using bagasse and molasses; and corn starch, glucose, and other related products under the Amryal, Hydex, and Vaalgold Gluten 60 brands. The company offers white and brown sugar products under the Huletts, Huletts SunSweet, Blue Crystal, and Marathon brands. It also engages in the ethanol production and electricity generation activities. Tongaat Hulett Limited was founded in 1875 and is based in Tongaat, South Africa.

Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited manufactures, markets, and distributes healthcare products primarily in Sub-Saharan Africa and India. It offers a portfolio of prescription medicines, generic products, critical care, over-the-counter and consumer products, intravenous solutions, blood collection products, and renal dialysis systems. The company provides pharmaceutical products in a range of therapeutic classes, such as women's health, antiretroviral, allergies, dermatology, cardiovascular, central nervous system, respiratory, ophthalmic, urology, pain, mental health, gastrointestinal, infections, pain and inflammation, colds and flu, personal care, supplements and energy, feminine hygiene, and digestive well-being. It also manufactures and supplies hospital and critical care products, including intravenous fluids, renal dialysis systems, products for the storage of blood and blood components, infusion systems, and accessories. Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited was founded in 1890 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Edcon Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a non-food retailer in South Africa. Its Edgars division operates department stores that primarily sell clothing, footwear, cosmetics, mobile phones, homewares, and accessories to middle to upper income consumers. This division operates the Edgars, Boardmans, Red Square, Edgars Active, Edgars Shoe Gallery, Inglot, La Senza, Accessorize, Topshop, Tom Tailor, Mac, Lipsy, Bobbi Brown, Lucky Brands, Dune, TM Lewin, Salsa, Jigsaw, Calvin Klein, Khiels, Victoria's Secret Beauty and Accessories, Vince Camuto, River Island, Dr. Martens, Express, and Jo Malone stores. The company's CNA division sells stationery, books, magazines, greeting cards, mobile phones, music, toys, and photographic and digital equipment to middle to upper income consumers. Its Discount division sells clothing, footwear, mobile phones, cosmetics, homewares, and accessories to lower and middle income consumers under the Jet brand, as well as with associated brands that include Jet Mart, and Legit. The company's Edgars Zimbabwe division offers clothing, footwear, cosmetics, mobile phones, and accessories under the Edgars and Jet formats to the lower, middle, and upper income consumers. Its Manufacturing division manufactures ladies and men's outerwear products, as well as footwear. The company's Credit and Financial Services division offers consumer credit and insurance products to trade debtors. As of 26 March, 2016, the company operated 1542 stores, including 213 in Namibia, Botswana, Lesotho, Swaziland, Mozambique, Ghana, Zimbabwe, and Zambia. Edcon Holdings Limited was founded in 1929 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Sun International Limited owns and operates casino, hotel, and resort properties in South Africa, other African countries, and Latin America. It operates or has an interest in a total of 18 resorts, luxury hotels, and casinos. Sun International Limited was incorporated in 1967 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

PPC Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells cementitious, aggregate, lime and limestone, and fly ash products in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Rwanda, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It offers premium Portland and Portland-composite cement products under the Surebuild, OPC, IDM, and Sureroad brands; unslaked lime, hydrated lime, limestone, FGD limestone, burned dolomite, and fine unslaked lime, as well as lump and burnt lime; aggregate products, such as road stones, concrete stones, supers sand, crusher sand, -2mm sand, river sand, building sand, plaster sand, base and sub-base materials, metallurgical dolomite, and agricultural lime; and ready mix concrete and dry mortar mix. The company was formerly known as Pretoria Portland Cement Company Limited and changed its name to PPC Ltd in October 2012. PPC Ltd was founded in 1892 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Impala Platinum Holdings Limited engages in mining, processing, refining, and marketing platinum and associated platinum group metals (PGMs) in South Africa and Zimbabwe. It operates through Mining Operations, Refining Services, Chrome Processing, and Other segments.

Trencor Limited, an investment holding company, owns, leases, manages, and trades in dry freight, tank, and refrigerated marine cargo containers worldwide. It is also involved in related financing activities, as well as in the collection of long-term receivables. The company was founded in 1929 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Oceana Group Limited operates as a fishing company. It operates through Canned Fish and Fishmeal; Fishmeal and Fish Oil; Horse Mackerel and Hake; Lobster, Squid and French Fries; and Commercial Cold Storage and Logistics segments. The company engages in fishing for inshore pelagic species, such as anchovy, the gulf menhaden species, redeye herring, and pilchard; the production, marketing, and distribution of fishmeal and canned fish products under the Lucky Star label, as well as pet foods under the Lucky Pet brand; and provision of fishmeal and fish oil for use in animal and aquaculture feed, fertilizers, pharmaceutical, and chemical industries. It is also involved in the fishing, processing, procurement, distribution, and trading of caught demersal species, such as horse mackerel, hake, monk, kingklip, and other by-catch products. In addition, the company produces and exports live and frozen South African rock lobster, and frozen squid products; and produces and markets nitrogen frozen lobsters and lobster tails, and French fries. Further, it owns and operates 12 public refrigerated warehouse facilities, as well as engages in fruit handling, blast freezing, and transportation activities; and offers logistic services. The company provides cold storage for products, such as poultry, fish, meat, vegetables, dairy, margarine, and fruit. It offers its products to individuals, retailers, wholesalers, importers, exporters, restaurants, food producers, feed manufacturers, and pet owners in Africa, the United States, Asia, the European Union, and Australia. Oceana Group Limited was incorporated in 1918 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Reunert Limited operates in the fields of electrical engineering, information communication technologies (ICT), and applied electronics in South Africa, Australia, Lesotho, Sweden, the United States, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. Its Electrical Engineering segment designs, manufactures, installs, and maintains power cables; manufactures and supplies copper and optical fiber telecommunications cables and cable ducts, as well as low-voltage distribution, protection, and control equipment; and supplies high and medium-voltage switchgears and transformers. This segment also provides power installations services; designs and manufactures overhead aluminum conductors; and manufactures copper casted rods. It serves mining, utilities, commercial, industrial, residential, retail, petrochemical, transport, power, and building sectors, as well as electrical contractors, equipment manufacturers, fixed and mobile network operators, municipalities, and parastatals. The company's ICT segment provides data and voice communication and network services and solutions, as well as asset-based rental solutions; and distributes office automation and telecommunication systems. This segment comprises corporate and retail customers, small and medium enterprises, government, and state-owned entities, non-profit organizations. Its Applied Electronics segment specializes in tactical VHF/UHF/HF communication systems; designs and manufactures fuses and related defense products for artillery, mortar, naval, and aircraft weapon systems; develops and manufactures ground and naval search and tracking radar systems; and designs and manufactures mining radar sensor systems used in open-cast mining. This segment manufactures and supplies remote-controlled weapon platforms; and supplies system engineering and logistic support services in telecommunications, radar, satellite, mining, fare management, and transportation fields. Reunert Limited was founded in 1888 and is headquartered in Woodmead, South Africa.
Murray & Roberts Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates in the construction and engineering, underground mining development, and oil and gas markets.

African Oxygen Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and distributes atmospheric gases, liquefied petroleum gas (LPG), and hard goods in South Africa and other African countries. It operates through Atmospheric Gases, LPG, Hard Goods, and Emerging Africa segments. The company offers atmospheric gases, such as industrial, special, medical, and hospitality gases. The company offers its products through direct pipelines and outlets to various industries, such as healthcare services, production of iron and steel, fabrication and assembly of motor vehicles, industrial ceramics, food preservation, and water treatment. It also provides LPG in cylinder sizes and bulk supplies to major industrial and hospitality users the Handigas brand name; and hard goods that include filler materials, arc equipment, rescue packs, regulators, and safety equipment. The company was founded in 1927 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. African Oxygen Limited is a subsidiary of The Linde Group.
Tiger Brands Limited engages in the manufacture and marketing of FMCG products to restaurants, catering services, and other out-of-home institutions primarily in Southern Africa.

addressline2: Corner of Main Reef Road and Ward Avenue
spbusinessdescription: Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited engages in the exploration and mining of gold in South Africa and Papua New Guinea. The company also explores for copper, silver, uranium, and molybdenum deposits.
Sappi Limited manufactures and sells dissolving wood pulp, paper pulp, paper based, and bio-refinery solutions to direct and indirect customers worldwide.

Cargo Carriers Limited provides technology-enabled solutions for logistics, transport, and aviation customers in sub-Saharan Africa. The company primarily operates through three divisions: Industrial, Agricultural, and Supply Chain Services. The Industrial division provides supply chain and logistic services to chemicals, gases, steel, powders, fuel and mining sectors with fleets of vehicles tailored to clients' individual needs and products. The Agricultural division provides expert logistics services, including the loading and haulage of products from the producer to the processor, as well as the distribution of processed agricultural products. This division focuses on the sugarcane sector. The Supply Chain Services division engages in the moving of diversified products and hazardous and non-hazardous cargo both within South Africa and across borders; provision of consulting and system implementation services; and the supply and deployment of logistics software and systems. Cargo Carriers Limited is also involved in provision of passenger aircraft transportation services; and property investment activities. The company was founded in 1956 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Cargo Carriers Limited is a subsidiary of Cargo Carriers Holdings (Pty) Ltd.

Prescient Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides financial and information management services in South Africa and internationally. The Financial Services segment offers investment management, fund services and administration, stockbroking, wealth management, and corporate advisory services, as well as retail and institutional retirement and insurance products. The Information Management Services segment provides healthcare administration services; and consulting and implementation services for data and management information software. The company was formerly known as PBT Group Ltd. Prescient Limited is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Hudaco Industries Limited, together with its subsidiaries, imports and distributes branded automotive, industrial, and electrical consumable products in the southern African region. It operates through two segments, Consumer-Related Products and Engineering Consumables. The Consumer-Related Products segment distributes clutch kits, automotive ignition leads, oil and hydraulic seals, wheels, brake and clutch hydraulics, mountings, bushes, hydraulic repair kits, cylinders, hoses, CV joints, wheel hubs, suspension components, and vehicle components to the automotive and industrial after-market; maintenance free lead acid, stand-by and solar batteries; power tools, marine engines, survey equipment, rivets, and fasteners; and intruder detection, access control, and related CCTV equipment, including design and integration of systems, fiber-optics, fire detection, and video over IP installations. This segment also distributes professional mobile radio equipment and radio systems integrators; wireless networking, VoIP, and video products; and communication management software, solutions, and equipment. The Engineering Consumables segment distributes diesel engines and spares, as well as support services; and geared motors, beltings, hydraulics, drivetrains, filtration solutions, kits and accessories, pneumatics, industrial hoses, conveyor drive pulleys, variable speed drives, special engineering steels, specialized thermoplastic pipes and fittings, gear pumps, ferrous and non-ferrous castings, electrical cablings, plugs, and related products to the manufacturing, mining, and agricultural aftermarkets. This segment also distributes bearings, chains, seals, geared motors, electric motors, and transmission products. The company primarily serves wholesale and retail, automotive, manufacturing, mining, security, alternative energy, construction, public, agricultural, and other sectors. Hudaco Industries Limited was founded in 1891 and is headquartered in Edenvale, South Africa.

The Foschini Group Limited operates independent chain-stores in South Africa and internationally. It offers clothing products, accessories, footwear, and cosmetics for ladies, men, teenagers, and kids; jewelry; cellphones; sporting and outdoor apparel and equipment; and homeware furniture. The company operates retail stores under various brand names comprising @home, @homelivingspace, American Swiss, Charles & Keith, Colette, DonnaClaire, Duesouth, Exact, Fabiani, The FIX, Foschini, G-Star Raw, hi, Markham, Mat & May, Next, Phase Eight, SODA Bloc, Sportscene, Sterns, Totalsports, and Whistles, as well as an e-commerce platform. It also provides services, including credit, insurance, publishing, mobile airtime, and rewards program to its customers. The company primarily serves middle and upper income groups. It operates 3,125 outlets in 31 countries. The company was formerly known as Foschini Limited and changed its name to The Foschini Group Limited in September 2010. The Foschini Group Limited was founded in 1924 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Metair Investments Limited manufactures, assembles, distributes, and retails energy storage products and automotive components in Africa, Europe, Turkey, the Middle East, and Russia. It offers energy storage products, including automotive and industrial batteries, solar systems, back-up systems, standby systems, charging systems, battery distribution networks, and lithium-ion starter batteries and mining cap lamps for automotive, telecom, utility, mining, retail, and materials/products handling sectors, as well as original equipment manufacturers. The company also provides automotive components, such as air-conditioning and climate control systems, cooling modules, washer systems, charge air coolers, and reserve tanks; radiators; air cleaners; wiper systems; electronic control units; starter motors; hydraulics, brake pads, brake discs, and brake shoes; coil springs, leaf springs, stabilizers, and torsion bars; and headlights, tail lights, reflectors, commercial lighting products, streetlights, and warehouse lights. Its automotive components also comprise plastic injection moldings, plastic bins/storage, and chrome plating on plastics; automotive cable, automotive wire, and wiring harnesses; combination meter/instrument clusters; and front-end modules, shock absorbers, struts, and track control arms. The company provides automotive components for use in the assembly of new vehicles; and industrial and utility sectors. Metair Investments Limited was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Pick n Pay Stores Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the retail of food, clothing, general merchandise, pharmaceuticals, and liquor. It operates through two segments, South Africa and Rest of Africa. The company owns, franchises, and invests in supermarkets, liquor stores, hypermarkets, clothing stores, and convenience stores under the Pick n Pay and Boxer brands, which offer groceries, clothing, food products, liquor, health and wellness products, pharmaceuticals, and general merchandise. It also offers products online. In addition, the company acquires and develops retail and distribution sites; and offers value-added services, which include financial services comprising cellular, third-party bill payments, pre-paid electricity, travel and event tickets, as well as sells gift cards. It operates retail stores in South Africa, Botswana, Namibia, Zambia, Zimbabwe, Ghana, and internationally. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Pick n Pay Stores Limited operates as a subsidiary of Pick n Pay Holdings Limited.

Allied Electronics Corporation Limited operates in power electronics, telecommunications, multimedia, and information technology industries in South Africa and internationally. It manufactures and supplies power, telecommunication, and control cables, as well as cable accessories; and designs and manufactures transformers and transformer-related products that are used in generation, transmission, and distribution networks, as well as transformer insulation and accessories. The company also manufactures and supplies batteries for use in automotive, telecom, uninterrupted power supply, and energy power sectors; and supplies system technology integration solutions to commercial and industrial power users, utility companies, and state enterprises. In addition, it offers communications services, including voice, data, video, and digital radio communication networks, as well as Internet services; designs and produces various multi-media and electronics products, such as set-top boxes; and distributes electronic components and products. Further, the company provides software and payment collection solutions to the micro-financial industry, as well as point-of-sale and PIN pad solutions for financial institutions. Allied Electronics Corporation Limited is headquartered in Parktown, South Africa.

eMedia Holdings Limited operates as a media investment holding company in South Africa. It offers television news services, as well as OpenView HD, a multi-channel platform; and holds investments in the television broadcasting and content creation sectors. The company also provides property and facilities services, including broadcast and television studios, post-production facilities, and equipment rental and sales. The company was formerly known as Seardel Investment Corporation Limited and changed its name to eMedia Holdings Limited in November 2015. eMedia Holdings Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. eMedia Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Hosken Consolidated Investment Limited.

RCL Foods Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the food business in South Africa. It processes and markets chicken under the Rainbow, Farmer Brown, Rainbow FoodSolutions, Epol, and Cobb brand names. The company also manufactures, markets, and distributes a range of food products comprising grain and edible oil-based products, sorghum, peanut butter, rusks, and pet foods, as well as salad dressings, dips, and spreads; meat pies under the Pieman's brand; and specialty products, such as sandwiches, muffins, desserts, snack foods, scones, rye breads, cake products, pastries, and croissants. In addition, it produces maize based health drink under the Mageu No 1, Smooth, Phuzimpilo, and Mnandi brands; and operates seven bakeries, one flour mill, and one maize mill. Further, the company engages in the production, marketing, sale, and distribution of sugar under the Selati brand; and manufactures animal feed from by-products of the sugar manufacturing process under the Molatek brand. Additionally, it provides third party logistics and sales service for frozen, chilled, and ambient goods. The company was formerly known as Rainbow Chicken Limited and changed its name to RCL Foods Limited in August 2013. RCL Foods Limited was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in Westville, South Africa. RCL Foods Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro Limited.

Delta EMD Limited does not have significant operations. Previously, it manufactured and supplied electrolytic manganese dioxide used in the production of alkaline batteries. The company was formerly known as Delta Electrical Industries Limited. Delta EMD Limited was founded in 1982 and is based in Nelspruit, South Africa.

ELB Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides engineering solutions to the mining, minerals, power, port, construction, and industrial sectors in the fields of materials handling, mineral separation, industrial projects, and power solutions in Africa and internationally. It operates in three segments: Equipment, Engineering Services, and Australasia. The company supplies construction equipment, such as trenching and horizontal directional drilling equipment, pneumatic piercing tools, backhoe loaders, compact wheel loaders, skid-steer loaders, motor graders, compact excavators, telescopic handlers, and compaction equipment. It also offers earthmoving equipment consisting of bulldozers, wheel loaders, and open cast mining trucks; and mining/recycling equipment, including mobile and static screening plants, mobile and static crushing plants, hydraulic drill rigs, hydraulic breakers, excavator attachments, recycling systems, block makers, heavy-duty rotary barrel screens, telescopic conveyor belts, vertical shaft impact crushers, screener-crusher buckets, modular plants, and washing systems. In addition, the company provides engineering services in the areas of bulk material handling, industrial projects, engineered technologies, mechanical/structural erection, conveyer maintenance, and logistics, as well as electrical, control, and instrumentation. Further, it imports, distributes, and maintains underground and utility construction equipment, and green waste processing equipment. The company was formerly known as Edward L Bateman Ltd. ELB Group Limited was founded in 1903 and is based in Boksburg, South Africa.

Exxaro Resources Limited, a diversified resources company, operates in the coal, titanium dioxide, ferrous, and energy markets in South Africa, Europe, and the United States. The company operates through Coal, Ferrous, and TiO2 and Alkali Chemicals segments. It produces thermal coal, metallurgical coal, and semi-soft coking coal products in the Waterberg and Mpumalanga regions. The company was formerly known as Kumba Iron Ore Limited and changed its name to Exxaro Resources Limited in November 2006. The company is based in Pretoria West, South Africa.
Telkom SA SOC Limited provides telecommunication services to wholesale, business, residential, and payphone customers in South Africa and internationally.

addressline2: Corner Fredman Drive and Rivonia Road
spbusinessdescription: FirstRand Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides banking, insurance, and investment products and services to retail, commercial, corporate, and public sector customers primarily in South Africa.

PSG Group Ltd, an investment holding company, provides diversified financial and other services. The company offers financial advice, stockbroking, asset management, insurance, financing, banking, investing, and corporate financial services. It also provides private school education services; energy saving solutions; private equity services; mine safety and support services; and logistics services, as well as engages in FMCG distribution, and agriculture and fruit businesses. PSG Group Ltd was founded in 1995 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Petmin Limited, a multi-commodity mining company, produces and sells metallurgical anthracite in South Africa and internationally. It operates through two segments, Anthracite and Expansion Projects. The company holds interests in the Somkhele anthracite mine located to the northwest of Richards Bay in KwaZulu-Natal; the North Atlantic Iron Corporation project, an iron sands deposit that produces and supplies merchant pig iron in Labrador, Canada; and the Veremo pig iron project located near Stofberg in Mpumalanga Province, South Africa. It also exports its products. Petmin Limited was incorporated in 1972 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. As of May 31, 2017, Petmin Limited was taken private.

Sasfin Holdings Limited provides banking and financial services to entrepreneurs, corporates, and high net-worth individuals primarily in South Africa. The company operates through Business Banking, Transactional Banking and Treasury, Wealth, Capital, and Commercial Solutions divisions. The Business Banking division offers equipment, taxi, and trade and debtor finance services. The Transactional Banking and Treasury division provides transactional banking products, such as deposits, transactional accounts, and debit cards; and treasury products and services. The Wealth division provides portfolio management and stockbroking, financial planning, asset management, asset consulting, healthcare, and fixed income products and services, as well as money market services. The Capital division offers private and property equity, and corporate finance services. The Commercial Solutions division offers foreign exchange, incentives, short-term insurance, and logistics services. Sasfin Holdings Limited was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Waverley, South Africa.

Spanjaard Limited manufactures and distributes specialized industrial and consumer lubricants, and allied chemical products worldwide. It operates in two segments, Special Lubricants and Allied Chemicals, and Metal Powders. The company also manufactures and sells various types and grades of metal powders. It serves the industrial, automotive, marine, mining, electrical, and household markets. The company was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Spanjaard Limited is a subsidiary of Spanjaard Group Limited.

Merafe Resources Limited engages in the mining and beneficiation of chrome ore in to ferrochrome. It serves stainless steel producers in South Africa, North America, the European Union, China, South Korea, Japan, India, and Taiwan. The company was founded 1987 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

Famous Brands Limited and its subsidiaries operates as a branded food service franchisor. The company operates through Franchising and Supply Chain divisions. Its casual dining brand portfolio comprises Wimpy, Mugg & Bean, Europa, Fego Caffe, Pubs, Tashas, Vovo Telo, House of Coffees, NetCafe, Keg, Turn n Tender, Coffee Couture, The Bread Basket, Mythos, and PAUL; and quick service brand portfolio include Steers, Debonairs Pizza, Fishaways, Milky Lane, Giramundo, Juicy Lucy, Mr Biggs, and Wakaberry. The company operates 2,614 franchised restaurants in South Africa, the Rest of Africa, the United Kingdom, and the Middle East. It also manufactures and supplies meat, sauces, spices, cheese, bakery items, ice cream, fruit juice, mineral water, coffee, and other hot beverage products to its franchisees, as well as to the retail trade and hospitality industries. The company was formerly known as Steers Holdings Limited and changed its name to Famous Brands Limited in 2004. Famous Brands Limited is based in Midrand, South Africa.

Alviva Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, distributes, and supports information and communication technology (ICT) hardware, software, and infrastructure products. The company operates through ICT Distribution, Services and Solutions, Financial Services, and Group Central Services segments. It offers servers, personal computers, notebooks, tablets, and mobile phones; copiers and printers; security, CCTV, fire detection and prevention, and access control systems; and office automation products, hardware and software products, and implementation and structured finance solutions. The company also provides managed services, technology solution integration, and business applications; and connectivity, communication, cloud, and software development services. In addition, it offers a range of financial products, including operating rentals for technology based equipment, hire and service agreements of equipment and ancillary services, insurance of technology based goods, and short term project finance of equipment. Further, the company distributes server racking, copper, fiber, wireless, and related network hardware; and structured cabling solutions and purpose-built electronic enclosures, as well as complementary infrastructure products, such as media converters, optical fiber CCTV, and co-axial for telecommunications, data, and telephony applications. Additionally, it offers rooftop and ground solar installation services for corporate customers. Alviva Holdings Limited operates in South Africa, Botswana, Namibia, Zambia, and Mozambique. The company was formerly known as Pinnacle Holdings Limited and changed its name to Alviva Holdings Limited in March 2017. Alviva Holdings Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

DRDGOLD Limited engages in the retreatment, production, and sale of gold from surface tailings in South Africa. It recovers gold from surface tailings in the central and western Witwatersrand basin in Gauteng province. The company was founded in 1895 and is based in Rosebank, South Africa.

Netcare Limited operates private hospitals in South Africa and the United Kingdom. It provides hospital, healthcare, and renal care networks, as well as emergency medical services. The company also offers occupational health and employee wellness services; and medical management services at commercial, industrial, construction, and mining sites. In addition, it operates primary care facilities for group medical practices, which provides access to general practitioners and dentists, radiology, pathology, pharmacy, physiotherapy, and day clinics. Further, the company provides dialysis services to patients with compromised kidney function; and operates retail pharmacies. As of December 6, 2016, the company operated 114 hospitals in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Lesotho, and Mozambique. Netcare Limited was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

addressline3: Maxwell Office Park, Magwa Crescent West
spbusinessdescription: Northam Platinum Limited engages in mining, refining, marketing, and selling platinum group metals and its by-products in Asia, South Africa, Europe, and North America. It explores for platinum, palladium, rhodium, gold, chrome, nickel sulphate, copper, and others. The company holds 100% interests in the Zondereinde mine covering approximately 7,625 hectares of land located in the northern portion of the western limb of the Bushveld complex; and the Booysendal mine comprising approximately 15,151 hectares of land located in the southern compartment of the eastern limb of the Bushveld complex. Northam Platinum Limited was incorporated in 1977 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Masonite (Africa) Limited owns and develops timber plantations in South Africa, rest of Africa, and Australasia. The company manufactures and distributes hardboards, such as original, tempered, cornice, brickliner, chalkboard, clipboard, underlay, layerpad, and pegboard hardboards, as well as Fincote hardboards; and softboards. It also offers door skins comprising pre-fabricated and untampered door skins as well as deep molded door panels. The company was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

Mustek Limited assembles and distributes personal computers and complementary information and communications technology (ICT) products in South Africa. The company offers 3D printing solutions; computing solutions; tablets; displays; led lighting solutions and solar panels; internal wireless PCIE cards, gigabit enterprise switches, powerline adapters, routers, and unified security gateways; printers and scanners; and flash memory storage solutions and external USBs. It also provides point-of-sale solutions; and security solutions, such as CCTV cameras, speed domes, access control systems, IP-surveillance systems, DVR and NVR systems, and accessories. The company offers its products under the Mecer brand. Mustek Limited was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Naspers Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides Internet and ecommerce, video-entertainment, and print media services worldwide. The company operates through Video Entertainment, Internet, and Media segments.

Rex Trueform Clothing Company Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the retail of clothing and fashion accessories in South Africa. It operates through Retail Trading Division, Property Division, and Group Services segments. The company offers ladies' and men's clothing, shoes, costume jewelry, related fashion accessories, and cosmetics through branded Queenspark outlets, as well as through Queenspark branded franchised outlets in Namibia and Kenya. It also develops and leases its commercial properties to third parties. The company was founded in 1937 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Rex Trueform Clothing Company Limited is a subsidiary of African and Overseas Enterprises Limited.

addressline2: South Wing, First Floor, Block A
spbusinessdescription: SA Corporate Real Estate Limited is a real estate investment trust. The firm invests in the real estate markets of South Africa. It primarily invests in industrial, retail, inner-city residential and commercial assets, primarily located in the major metropolitan centers of South Africa. SA Corporate Real Estate Limited is based in South Africa.

Andulela Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the processing and distribution of steel products in Southern Africa. The company offers steel products, including welded universal columns or beams and T-beams; a range of roofing solutions; fencing and wire products; tubing and cold formed flat and long products; and value added services. It also produces and sells platinum group metals, including platinum, palladium, rhodium, and gold, which are recovered through reprocessing of tailings concentrate. The company is based in Sandton, South Africa. Andulela Investment Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Newshelf 1005 Proprietary Limited.

Illovo Sugar Limited produces and sells sugar and downstream products. The company offers industrial sugar, including refined bulk sugar primarily to soft drink, confectionery, canning, and re-packing customers; refined and brown pre-pack sugar under the Illovo, Whitespoon, and Bwana Sukari names for retail and wholesale customers; bulk raw sugar for refining; specialty sugars; and syrup products. Its downstream products include ethanol, furfural and furfuryl alcohol, diacetyl, 2.3-pentanedione, agricultural nematicides, natural methanol, ethanol potable extra neutral alcohol, anhydrous alcohol, rectified extra neutral alcohol, industrial alcohol, and lactulose. The company's downstream products also comprise Crop Guard that is used as an agricultural contact nematicide at planting; MultiGuard Protect, which is developed and marketed as an agricultural contact-nematicide; Protect that is used as a nematicide and fungicide prior to planting; and BioMass Sugar, which is used as phytofortifiers/soil improvers or as liquid organic fertilizers. It is also involved in cane growing and electricity exports activities. The company markets its products in Malawi, Mozambique, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, and Zambia. Illovo Sugar Limited also exports its products primarily to the European Union and the United States. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa. Illovo Sugar Limited is a subsidiary of ABF Overseas Limited.

addressline3: Cnr William Nicol and Wedgewood Link
spbusinessdescription: Adcorp Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides permanent recruitment and flexible staffing, professional, business process outsourcing, training, and financial services in South Africa, the rest of Africa, Singapore, and Australia. It operates through Group Central Cost, Traditional Staffing and Contracting Business, and New Generation Business segments. The company also offers workforce management and resourcing, selection, managed services provider, vendor management systems, functional outsourcing, HR consulting, analytics, and advisory services. In addition, it provides project management, agency agreement, and IT services. The company serves mining and mineral, oil and gas, construction, forestry and paper, chemicals, healthcare, hospitality and leisure, logistics, FMCG, steel and other metals, food processors and producers, beverages, pharmaceuticals, personal and household care, general retail, banking and finance, transport, telecom, humanitarian, support services, IT and technology, media, and government sectors. The company was founded in 1968 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

Assore Limited, a mining holding company, engages in base minerals and metals ventures business. The company involved in mining iron, manganese, and chrome ores, as well as producing manganese and chrome alloys. It also mines for wonderstone, a type of pyrophyllite that is used to produce high-precision components; and produces wear and acid-resistant tiles, which are installed in various mining, industrial, and filtration applications. In addition, the company is involved in ceramic business. It serves customers in the Far East, Europe, the United States, South Africa, and internationally. The company was incorporated in 1950 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Assore Limited is a subsidiary of Oresteel Investments Proprietary Limited.

The Bidvest Group Limited operates as a services, trading, and distribution company. It operates through seven divisions: Automotive, Commercial Products, Electrical, Financial Services, Freight, Office & Print, and Services. It retails motor vehicles, including passenger cars, SUVs, and trucks, as well as provides parts and tires support services; and distributes electrical, cable and allied products, and solutions and services for corporate, commercial, industrial, and mining customers, as well as for residential and large-scale infrastructural projects. The company also offers various banking and financial products and services to corporate and individual customers; air freight and ocean freight services; logistics and supply chain solutions; and transport, warehousing, stevedoring, container and bulk handling, customs clearing and forwarding, and ship agency services. In addition, it manufactures packaging products, fasteners and closures, self-adhesive tapes, and catering equipment; manufactures and distributes brushware and consumables, as well as distributes machinery and accessories to the clothing industry; distributes office products and furniture, office automation, and software solutions, as well as print, packaging, labelling, and communication products; and distributes food products. Further, the company offers facility management, security, industrial, and allied services; horse-mackerel, canned pilchards, oysters, and other fish products; new and pre-owned vehicles, financing and insurance products, parts and accessories, and after-sales services; foreign exchange services, prepaid world currency cards, and money transfer services; and IT services, including data management, networking, servers, software, hardware, and IT related services. Additionally, it provides property management and development, and assistance services. The Bidvest Group Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

African Media Entertainment Limited operates as a radio broadcasting company in South Africa. The company's Algoa FM broadcasts music, news and gossip, sports information, and local traffic and weather information in the Eastern Cape; and OFM offers adult contemporary and golden oldie sounds to deliver an upscale audience between the ages of 25 and 49 in Free State, North West Province, Northern Cape, northern KZN, and southern Gauteng. It also operates United Stations, a specialist radio sales house; and RadioHeads, a radio station that provides radio solutions, including media planning and buying, creative strategy, and copywriting, as well as an editing suite to create final product. The company is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Distribution and Warehousing Network Limited operates in the building materials and fixtures sector in the Republic of South Africa and internationally. The company operates in three segments: Building, Infrastructure, and Solutions. It engages in the manufacture and wholesale trading of hardware, sanitaryware, bathroomware, plumbing, kitchen, brushware, and other building material products, as well as welding equipment and consumables. The company is also involved in the manufacture and wholesale trading of engineering, civil products, pipes and pipe fittings, valves, plastics, and related accessories. It primarily serves building merchants, and local and provincial governments and contractors. The company is headquartered in Germiston, the Republic of South Africa.

Cullinan Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a tourism and leisure company in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Travel and Tourism, Marine and Boating, and Financial Services. It offers wholesale, retail, and coaching and touring travel services. The company also provides marine and boating equipment to boat builders and wholesalers, as well as operates two retail shops in Cape Town. In addition, it offers credit, bridging, and marine finance. The company was founded in 1901 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Cullinan Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Alpine Asset Management Limited.

Grindrod Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in freight services, shipping, trading, and financial services businesses worldwide. The company's Freight Services division offers freight logistics services, such as road transportation, rail, intermodal solutions, warehousing, storage, stevedoring, seafreight, ships agency, travel agency, and traditional logistics services; and operates terminals and ports. This division provides its services for the movement of dry-bulk, bulk liquid, containerized cargo, and vehicles along import/export corridors. Its Shipping division operates a fleet of owned, long-term chartered, and joint-venture dry-bulk, liquid-bulk, container, and bunker vessels. This division focuses on moving dry bulk cargo, such as minerals, coal, ores, and agricultural products, as well as clean petroleum products. The company's Financial Services division offers commercial lending solutions, including term loans, mezzanine finance, and equity funding; invoice discounting and trade finance products; cash deposits, investment products, and exchange traded funds; and commercial and industrial property finance, property private equity, and property investment options. This division also provides card solutions; preference-share investments and treasury deposits; corporate finance products; and asset management services, including wealth management services for private clients and institutional fund management services. Grindrod Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Investec Limited, a specialist bank and asset manager, provides a range of financial products and services to South Africa, the United Kingdom, Europe, Asia/Australia, and internationally. It operates through three divisions: Asset Management, Wealth & Investment, and Specialist Bank. The Asset Management division manages investments of private and public sector pension funds, insurers and corporates, and foundations and central banks, as well as intermediaries serving individual investors through equity, fixed income, multi-asset, and alternative investments. The Wealth & Investment division provides wealth management, portfolio management, private office, and stockbroking services to individuals, families, trusts, and charities, as well as alternative investment, investment advisory, electronic trading, and retirement and succession planning services. The Specialist Banking division offers private banking products and services, such as deposits, lending and investment products, transactional banking and foreign exchange services; corporate and institutional banking services, including treasury and trading, specialized lending, funds, debt capital markets, institutional research sales and trading, and advisory services; and property investment, and property investment fund management services. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Limited is a subsidiary of Investec Group Limited.

Invicta Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in trading engineering consumables, capital equipment, and building materials primarily in Southern Africa. It offers engineering consumables, including bearings, seals and gaskets, power transmission, material handling, fasteners, geared and electric drives, motors, and tools; fluid technology products and solutions, such as hydraulic, pneumatic, filtration, and lubrication; and technical design, on-site installation, maintenance, breakdown, and condition monitoring, as well as design engineering and failure analysis services. The company also engages in the wholesale and retail distribution of agricultural machinery, implements and related spares, heavy earthmoving machinery for construction and mining applications, material handling equipment and related spares, aftermarket replacement parts of earthmoving equipment, and heavy earthmoving machinery parts and diesel engine components, as well as operates as a distributor of Hyundai construction equipment. It is involved in the import, package, distribution, and wholesale of plumbing; manufactures PVC, HDPE, LDPE, polypropylene pipes, and fittings; and exports buildings supplies, as well as in a diversified flooring business. In addition, the company engages in the wholesale and retail of light earthmoving machinery, turf-grooming machinery, golf cars, utility vehicles, and related spares. Further, it holds properties. Invicta Holdings Limited is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

SacOil Holdings Limited, an independent oil and gas company, engages in the exploration and production of oil and gas properties. It holds interests in exploration and production assets located in Egypt, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Malawi, and Botswana. The company also distributes fuel products, such as diesel, petrol, and paraffin to local and national government, mining, construction, transport, manufacturing, parastatal, reseller, and agricultural clients in South Africa; trades in crude oil in Nigeria; and has a terminal project in Equatorial Guinea. The company was formerly known as SA Mineral Resources Corporation Limited and changed its name to SacOil Holdings Limited in December 2008. SacOil Holdings Limited was incorporated in 1993 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

Basil Read Holdings Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa and internationally. It operates through five segments: Construction, Developments, Mining, Roads, and St Helena. The company engages in the civil engineering, road construction, building, mixed-use integrated housing developments, property development, opencast mining, and blasting and excavating. It undertakes civil engineering and building projects, including earthworks, bridges, pipelines, infrastructure, harbor and marine works, industrial plants, sports facilities, roads, highways, and related industrial activities, as well as offers build-operate-transfer contracts, design and construct, and alternative solutions. The company is also involved in the surface contract mining, which includes drill, blast, load, haul, dump, material handling, and processing services to the mining, quarrying, and construction industries. In addition, it provides mine design, infrastructure development, planning, scheduling, operations management, and surveying and optimization services. Further, the company focuses on large-scale mixed income integrated housing developments for government, parastatals, and non-governmental organizations. Additionally, it designs, builds, and operates the St Helena airport project on the island of St Helena. The company was founded in 1952 and is headquartered in Boksburg, South Africa.

addressline3: Corner Homestead Avenue and Main Road
spbusinessdescription: City Lodge Hotels Limited engages in the hotel business in South Africa and internationally. It has 5 Courtyard Hotels with 381 suites; 17 City Lodge Hotels with 3,001 rooms; 12 Town Lodges with 1,503 rooms; 22 Road Lodges with 2,059 rooms; and the Fairview Hotel with 120 rooms. The company was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

Datatec Limited provides ICT solutions and services worldwide. The company's Westcon-Comstor segment distributes security, unified communications, networking, and data center products to value added resellers, systems integrators, and service providers. The company's Logicalis segment offers information technology (IT) solutions and managed services comprising IT infrastructure and networking solutions, communications and collaboration, data center, cloud, and managed services to various markets, including financial service, telecommunications, media and technology, education, healthcare, retail, manufacturing, and professional service markets, as well as to the government. Its Corporate, Consulting and Financial Services segment provides strategic, trusted advisory, modeling, and market intelligence services to the telecom, media, and technology industries; and strategic, technical, and operational advisory services to the public and private sectors. The company was founded in 1986 and is based in Sandown, South Africa.

Distell Group Limited, an investment holding company, produces, markets, and distributes alcoholic beverages and other non-alcoholic items in South Africa and internationally. The company offers ciders and ready-to-drinks under the Hunter's, Savanna, Bernini, and Esprit brands; and wines under the 4th Street, Nederburg, Drostdy-Hof, Autumn Harvest Crackling, Original Paarl Perle, J.C. Le Roux, Sedgwick's Old Brown, Two Oceans, Durbanville Hills, Pongracz, Fleur du Cap, Neethlingshof, OBiKWA, Earthbound Wines, Plaisir de Merle, Alto, Allesverloren, Zonnebloem Wines, Cellar Cask, and Autumn Harvest Crackling brands.It also provides spirits primarily under the Amarula, Scottish Leader, Klipdrift, Richelieu, Viceroy, Three Ships Whisky, Oude Meester, Knights Whisky, Bain's Cape Mountain Whisky, Van Ryn's, Black Bottle, Bisquit Cognac, Bunnahabhain, and Deanston Whisky brands. The company was founded in 1925 and is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. Distell Group Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro-Capevin Investments Proprietary Limited.

Group Five Limited engages in investments and concessions, manufacturing, and engineering and construction in South Africa and internationally. Its investments and concessions business develops, invests in, and operates transport concessions under the Intertoll brand, including toll motorways; develops infrastructure concessions, such as public buildings and power concessions; and invests in and develops commercial, industrial, retail, and residential properties. The company's manufacturing business provides ceiling boards, internal and external cladding boards, fascia boards and embossed building planks, barge boards, and a range of pipe products and building columns for residential and industrial applications; and steel products consisting of reinforcing steel bars, welded building mesh, binding wire and brick force, and large bore spirally welded coated and lined steel pipes. Its engineering and construction business operates as a contractor for building and housing projects; undertakes a range of heavy civil, infrastructure, roads, and earthworks contracts for public and private clients; operates as a contractor for structural, mechanical, electrical instrumentation, and piping projects; offers nuclear construction services; and provides turnkey engineer, procure, and construct (EPC) contracting services. Group Five Limited was founded in 1878 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Jasco Electronics Holdings Limited provides solutions in the areas of telecommunications, information technology, energy, and industry in South Africa and internationally. The company offers contact center solutions; unified communications solutions, including telephony, messaging systems, conferencing, analytics and reporting, and integration; and IT infrastructure solutions, such as data networking, connectivity, intelligent systems, professional, and managed services. It also engages in the design, installation, and maintenance of smart technology solutions for security and fire applications; and provision of smart building solutions covering rooftop management, telecommunications, power, renewable energy, security, fire, IT infrastructure, and building management. In addition, the company offers a range of infrastructure products and services for access, transmission, and operational support systems, and outside plant, as well as rents space on its existing infrastructure to telecommunications operators and service providers; and data center services. Further, it designs, builds, installs, integrates, and maintains video and audio solutions for broadcasters, as well as production and post-production houses; provides power solutions for UPS, generators, transformers, voltage stabilizers, and surge protection and monitoring equipment; and offers photovoltaic energy production solutions, as well as integrated water network management and event management solutions. Additionally, the company manufactures components for plastic injection mouldings and metal pressings, as well as manufactures and assembles wire harness products for the domestic appliance industry; offers paint and print solutions for plastic moulded components; provides electrical plugs, adaptors, and extensions under the Snapper brand; and manufactures salt water chlorination systems. Jasco Electronics Holdings Limited was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Nu-World Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, imports, assembles, markets, and distributes branded consumer durables in South Africa, Australia, Hong Kong, and the United Arab Emirates. It offers consumer electronics, hi-tech products, small electrical appliances, white goods, liquors, and furniture. The company was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Omnia Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides customized chemical solutions for the agriculture, mining, and chemicals sectors in South Africa and internationally. Its Agriculture segment produces and sells granular, liquid, and specialty fertilizers for farmers, co-operatives, and wholesalers. The company's Mining segment provides bulk emulsion and blended bulk explosives formulations for the opencast mining industry; produces electronic delay detonators and shocktube initiating systems; manufactures packaged explosives for underground mining and specialized surface blasting operations; offers emulsion explosives products and pumping equipment; and provides value-added services, including Protea Process, a service that covers the design of equipment, logistics, and on-site management. Its Chemicals segment manufactures and distributes specialty, functional, and effect chemicals and polymers. This segment also manufactures and distributes chemicals, which are used for the treatment of potable water. Omnia Holdings Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

Middle East Diamond Resources Limited engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral projects primarily in the Bushveld Complex, South Africa. The company primarily holds interest in four platinum group metal project areas, such as Abrina, Klipfontein, Doornpoort, and Syferfontein, as well as a group of seven other project areas; and Syferfontein, an iron ore/vanadium project. It has prospecting rights for platinum group metals across 63000 hectares in the Gauteng, Northwest, and Limpopo provinces of South Africa. The company was formerly known as Sable Metals and Minerals Limited and changed its name to Middle East Diamond Resources Limited in February 2016. Middle East Diamond Resources Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Bowler Metcalf Limited manufactures and sells plastics and plastic moldings in South Africa. The company offers rigid plastic packaging for the toiletry, cosmetic, household, pharmaceutical, and food markets. It also owns various properties. The company was founded in 1972 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Cashbuild Limited retails building materials and associated products. The company offers cement, roofing products, openings, timber, bricks, decorative, plumbing, hardware, ceilings, electrical, tools, and other products. It serves home builders and improvers, contractors, farmers, traders, and other customers. The company operates 238 stores in South Africa, Namibia, Lesotho, Botswana, Swaziland, and Malawi. Cashbuild Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Combined Motor Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the retail motor dealership, car hire, and distribution and franchising businesses in South Africa. It also provides financial and support, and maintenance leasing and insurance services. The company is headquartered in Umhlanga Ridge, South Africa.

Crookes Brothers Limited, together with its subsidiaries, produces primary agricultural products in South Africa, Swaziland, Mozambique, and Zambia. Its products include sugar cane, bananas, deciduous fruits, macadamia nuts, and grains, as well as vegetables, such as potatoes and tomatoes. The company also engages in the property development; rental of buildings and housings; travel and tourism business; plant nursery activities; and sale of sand and stones. Crookes Brothers Limited was founded in 1860 and is headquartered in Mount Edgecombe, South Africa.

addressline2: Cnr William Nicol Drive and Peter Place
spbusinessdescription: Italtile Limited operates as a franchisor and retailer of tiles, sanitaryware, bathware, laminated flooring, and other related home-finishing products in South Africa and internationally. The company's product portfolio includes tiles, bathware, and related products, bath and toilet products, showers, cabinets, taps, various related tools, adhesives, tile care products, paints, ceiling decors, hardware products, and accessories. It also invests in properties; and imports and distributes brassware, accessories, tiling tools, laminated floor boards, cabinets, and decors, as well as imports polished and glazed porcelain tiles. As of June 30, 2016, it operated a network of 146 stores in Southern and East Africa under the Italtile Retail, CTM, and TopT brands. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa. Italtile Limited is a subsidiary of Rallen Proprietary Limited.

KAP Industrial Holdings Limited engages in the supply chain, passenger transport, timber, chemical, automotive components, and bedding businesses in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Diversified Logistics and Diversified Industrial segments. The Diversified Logistics segment provides specialized transport, distribution, warehousing logistics, and supply chain re-engineering services to the mining and infrastructure, manufacturing, industrial, petrochemical, food, agriculture, and allied sectors. This segment also provides transport services to commuter, personnel, intercity, and tourism markets. The Diversified Industrial segment manufactures and distributes sawn timber, poles, wood-based panel products, decorative laminates, and solid surfacing materials; urea formaldehyde and polyethylene terephthalate resins for use in beverages and packaging industries; automotive components; and foam, fabrics, springs, and bases, as well as assembles mattresses. The company is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. KAP Industrial Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Steinhoff International Holdings Limited.

Tsogo Sun Holdings Limited engages in hospitality, gaming, and entertainment businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company operates approximately 100 hotels MAIA Luxury Resort & Spa, 54 on Bath, Beverly Hills, Palazzo, Sandton Sun, Suncoast Towers, Southern Sun Hotels, Southern Sun Resorts, Paradise Sun, Riverside Sun, Sabi River Sun, Tete Ferry Sun, SunSquare, The Caledon Hotel, Gold Reef City Theme Park Hotel, Garden Court, StayEasy, SUN1, InterContinental Hotels, Crowne Plaza, and Holiday Inn brand names in South Africa, Nigeria, Kenya, Tanzania, Zambia, Mozambique, the United Arab Emirates, and the Seychelles. It also operates 14 casinos and entertainment destinations under the Montecasino, Gold Reef City, Silverstar, The Caledon, Mykonos, Garden Route, Hemingways, Queens, Goldfields, Suncoast, Golden Horse, Blackrock, Emnotweni, and The Ridge names; and approximately 250 conference and banqueting facilities, as well as theatres, cinemas, restaurants, and bars. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Fourways, South Africa.

Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and supplies branded and generic pharmaceutical products, infant nutritionals, and consumer healthcare products. The company offers various branded products for a range of therapeutic categories, including anaesthetics, analgesics, anti-retrovirals, blood and haemopoetic, cardio vascular system, central nervous system, endocrine system, gastro-intestinal tract, infant milk formulations, musculo-skeletal agents, NSAIDs, oncology, oral hygiene, respiratory system, and urinary tract system, as well as ear, nose, and throat. It also provides various generics covering a range of categories, such as anti-depressants; analgesics for pain relief; anti-hypertensives for high blood pressure; bronchodilators for the treatment of asthma; anti-bacterials to treat bacterial infections; anti-gout agents; anti-inflammatory agents; anti-fungal agents; anti-histamines for the treatment of allergies; decongestants; gastro-intestinal agents; dermatologicals; and anti-retrovirals. In addition, the company manufactures narcotic and specialist fine active pharmaceutical ingredients. The company serves pharmacies, retail pharmacy chains, hospitals, clinics, prescribing specialists, dispensing general practitioners, managed healthcare funders, and retail stores across the private and public sectors. It has operations in South Africa, the Asia Pacific, Europe CIS, Latin America, Sub-Saharan Africa, the Middle East, North Africa, the United States, and Canada. Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates private hospitals primarily in South Africa. It operates through two divisions, Hospital and Healthcare Services. The Hospital division provides services to the private medically insured market with general hospital facilities that include intensive care units, high care units, operating theatres, emergency units, maternity units, and cardiac units, as well as other specialized facilities that provide inpatient or outpatient services in the areas of acute rehabilitation, chronic renal dialysis, mental healthcare services, and radiation and chemotherapy oncology. The Healthcare Services division offers acute and long term chronic hospitalization services to state patients; and primary and occupational healthcare services to employer groups in commerce, industry, parastatels, mining, and correctional services. It also provides long term care services to chronically ill, mental health, and frail care patients; and operates district hospital providing acute care to indigent patients, as well as manages customer owned clinics. In addition, this division operates learning college, which offers undergraduate and post graduate diplomas in nursing education, management, and clinical practice; and a foundation that provides financial sponsorship, as well as hospital and nursing services. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited operates a network of 63 hospitals in Johannesburg, Pretoria, Cape Town, Durban, Port Elizabeth, East London, and Bloemfontein. The company was formerly known as Afrox Healthcare Limited and changed its name to Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited in January 2005. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Illovo, South Africa.

Argent Industrial Limited manufactures and trades in steel and steel-related products worldwide. It operates through five divisions: Manufacturing, Steel Trading, Automotive, Watch List, and Properties. The company manufactures specialized industrial rubber mouldings; steel office and industrial furniture products; wrought iron style gates, wooden gates, wrought iron railings, decking panels, gate automation products, fixtures and fittings, posts, security products, and bonfires/wood burners; fencing products, metal deck panels, and garden arches; and castors and wheels, fibreglass and aluminum ladders, aluminum scaffolding equipment, pallet trucks, storage systems, trolleys, conveyors, scafflites, rolasteps, and access equipment. It also manufactures and distributes decorative paint and coating products, industrial paint products, wood and floor coatings, curtain suspensions, castor packs, brushware, aluminum extrusions, and straight edges and trolleys; toilets and sanitation systems; and fireplaces, speed control systems, and scrapers. In addition, the company supplies vehicle accessories; aluminum products; readymix concrete and mortars; steel plates, hot rolled sheets, galvanized sheets, heavy and light sections, tubing products, cold formed sections, and roof sheeting products; and tooling to furniture industry. Further, it retails home and security related products; manufactures a range of anti-burglar protection and security products; and rents properties. Additionally, the company provides concrete building products. Argent Industrial Limited was founded in 1972 and is based in La Lucia, South Africa.

addressline1: Cnr William Dabs and Old Paarl Roads
spbusinessdescription: Shoprite Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates as a food retailer and wholesaler. It operates through four segments: Supermarkets RSA, Supermarkets Non-RSA, Furniture, and Other Operating Segments.
