Mr Price Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a fashion-value retailer serving women, men, and children in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Apparel, Home, Financial Services and Cellular, and Central Services segments.

Transpaco Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, recycles, and distributes paper and plastic packaging products primarily in South Africa. It operates through Plastics Products, and Paper and Board Products segments. The company manufactures refuse bags, flexible plastic packaging solutions, recycled pre and post-consumer waste polyethylene, and specialized films; and printed folded cartons and package inserts, as well as spirally wound tubular cardboard cores, carton dividers, void fillers, and angle boards. Its products include black, clear, and color refuse bags, bin liners, and sheeting and films; light, medium, and heavy duty products; retail vest-type plastic bags, retail boutique plastic bags, industrial plastic bags, tubing and sheeting, and scholastic stationery; high and low density polyethylene; and cast pallet stabilization wrappings, stretch films, and layer cast films. The company also provides heavy and light duty cores, yarn and tape cores, conical containers, void fillers, carton dividers, and angle boards; and corrugated boards and cartons, pallet and food wraps, paper bags, tapes and closures, cleaning materials, protective clothing, papers and boards, and packaging machinery. In addition, it distributes packaging products. The company serves retail, industrial, agricultural, mining, pharmaceutical, and automotive sectors. Transpaco Limited is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

AfroCentric Investment Corporation Limited, an investment holding company, provides health administration and health risk management solutions to the healthcare funding industry in South Africa. Its services include, claims processing; client member contact centers; scheme finance management; hospital and medicine benefit management programs; disease management programs; hospital, general practitioner, specialist, optical, and dental networks; negotiations and strategic purchasing of healthcare services on behalf of clients; actuarial and health informatics and analysts; evaluation of technologies, pharmaceuticals, and clinical practices, as well as formulation of clinical health funding policies; and forensic services. The company also offers healthcare management systems for specialized diseases, network connectivity services, and outsourced technology solutions; actuarial prevalence assessment, financial impact analysis, HIV counselling and testing, education and awareness programs, workplace policies and procedures, and corporate treatment programs, as well as knowledge, attitudes, and practice surveys; and treatment for various musculoskeletal disorders, such as back, neck, shoulder, hip, and knee. In addition, it is involved in the provision of pharmacy courier services and services to various medical aid schemes; supply of chronic medication; and operation of information technology platform for clinical information management and pharmaceutical care. AfroCentric Investment Corporation Limited was founded in 2006 and is based in Roodepoort, South Africa.

Bell Equipment Limited manufactures, distributes, and exports various heavy and materials handling equipment primarily for agriculture, forestry, waste handling, construction, and mining and quarrying industries worldwide. The company offers articulated dump trucks (ADT), crawler dozers, dumper trailers, excavators, low profile ADT, motor graders, tractor loader backhoes, and wheeled loaders; and feller bunchers, forwarders, harvesters, loggers, long range forwarders, skidders, timber trucks, and waratah heads. It also provides articulated tractors, cane loaders, cane slew loaders, forklifts, haulage tractors, and tandem trailers; and asphalt construction, earth and sanitary landfill construction, light, stabilization and recycling, and waste management equipment. In addition, the company offers cone crushers, impact crushers, jaw crushers, and screens; and wheel conversions, bell versa trucks, cane cranes, coal bodies, rockscalers, TLB variations, and water tankers, as well as ADT concrete mixers, container trucks, fire trucks, and hook lift trucks. Further, it provides lubecheck systems, lubricants, simulators, fleet management systems, pre-owned equipment, rebuilt components, and replacement parts; and financing, training, maintenance, and warranty services. The company sells its products primarily through a network of outlets and independent dealers. Bell Equipment Limited was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Richards Bay, South Africa.
Imperial Holdings Limited engages in the logistics, vehicle, and financial service businesses in South Africa and internationally.

Wilson Bayly Holmes-Ovcon Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa, rest of Africa, and Australia. The company operates through five segments: Building and Civil Engineering, Roads and Earthworks, Australia, Property Developments, and Construction Materials segments. Its building and construction projects include healthcare and pharmaceutical facilities; special projects; leisure, recreation, and education facilities; concessions and property development; hotels and resorts; office and commercial buildings; residential and retail projects; and golf estates. The company also undertakes civil engineering projects comprising heavy industrial plants, mining projects, reservoirs, water and effluent treatment facilities, power plants, industrial buildings, silos and towers, and water control and marine works. In addition, it constructs toll roads and freeways; roads and rehabilitation projects; airports, harbors, and railways; dams; bulk earthworks; pipelines and infrastructures; and bridges and structures. Further, the company develops and sells properties, as well as manufactures and sells long-steel products. Wilson Bayly Holmes-Ovcon Limited was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Santam Ltd provides various general insurance products in South Africa and internationally. It offers personal insurance products, including car, building, home contents, and watercraft insurance; and SOS services, such as road side and medical emergency, household emergency, and legal advice services. The company also provides commercial insurance products comprising business, dental, guesthouse, medical, tourism, leisure and entertainment, and small business insurance. In addition, it offers specialist insurance products, such as marine, aviation, bonds and guarantees, cell captive, private client, corporate property, hospitality industry, seamless product, travel, heavy haulage, liability, taxi, and specialist real estate, and engineering insurance; and agriculture insurance products, including crop and asset insurance. The company was founded in 1918 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa. Santam Ltd is a subsidiary of Sanlam Ltd.

Sovereign Food Investments Limited produces and sells poultry products in South Africa. It is involved in breeding, broiler farming, food processing, animal feed milling, and value-added poultry processing and trading activities. The company offers its products under the Country Range and Cater Chicken brands, as well as various private labels and further processed brands. Sovereign Food Investments Limited was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Uitenhage, South Africa.

York Timber Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the commercial forestry, softwood sawmilling, plywood manufacturing, and timber trading businesses in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Processing Plants, Forestry, and Wholesale. It produces and sells a range of structural and industrial sawn timber products; and plywood timber products. In addition, the company owns plantations in the Mpumalanga province on which it grows pine and eucalyptus trees. It owns 93,988 hectares of land. The company was formerly known as The York Timber Organisation Limited and changed its name to York Timber Holdings Limited in May 2009. York Timber Holdings Limited was incorporated in 1916 and is based in Sabie, South Africa.
Bid Corp operates as a subsidiary of The Bidvest Group Limited.

MTN Group Limited operates in the telecommunications industry. It offers voice, data, access, virtual private network, and cloud solutions. It also provides digital services, such as mobile money account; and entertainment services, including MTN Football, Music, and Play.

Metrofile Holdings Limited provides records management and a range of customer services in South Africa. The company focuses on the various aspects of enterprise records and information management, including archival, storage, retrieval, and destruction of records; conversion of paper and analogue records to digital formats; rotation management and storage of backup media; professional consultancy and records management software; waste paper collection and recycling; and sale and maintenance of document handling equipment, as well as offers business and IT continuity services. It also sells and maintains a range of business equipment, including exam marking systems, library security systems and solutions, scanners, mail handling machines, packaging plants, employee management systems, visitor management software, microfilm solutions, and a range of ICT products, such as dustless keyboards for operating theatres. The company was formerly known as MGX Holdings Limited and changed its name to Metrofile Holdings Limited in February 2005. Metrofile Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Sentula Mining Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a diversified mining company in South Africa. The company operates through five segments: Opencast Mining and Earthmoving, Exploration Drilling, Overburden Drilling and Blasting, Crane Hire, and Coal Mining. Its opencast mining and earthmoving operations include movement and management of various aspects of overburden removal, as well as coal extraction and chrome mining. The company also provides outsourced mining and rehabilitation services; and sells equipment, spares, and anthracite. In addition, it engages in the hiring out of medium to heavy duty mobile cranes with capacities ranging from 25 to 220 tonnes. Sentula Mining Limited was incorporated in 1992 based in Woodmead, South Africa.

Tradehold Limited, an investment holding company, owns, manages, and leases real estate properties in the United Kingdom, South Africa, Namibia, Botswana, Zambia, Mozambique, and other African countries. Its properties include retail, serviced offices, industrial, residential, and leisure properties. The company is also involved in the investment and development of commercial properties; provision of treasury and debt factoring services, and asset-backed and short-term loans to small and medium-sized businesses, as well as invoice discounting, secured loans, incremental housing finance, specialized finance, and outsourced credit administration for asset finance. Tradehold Limited is based in San Gwann, Malta.

Super Group Limited engages in supply chain management, dealerships, and fleet management activities primarily in sub-Saharan Africa, Australia, New Zealand, the United Kingdom, and rest of Europe. The company's Supply Chain division provides supply chain services, including supply chain optimization, consulting, technology, procurement, third party distribution, transport, multi-temperature controlled product distribution, bulk raw material transportation, warehousing, inbound and outbound freight forwarding, customs clearing, import and export consolidation, international airfreight, and bonded cross-border transportation services. This division primarily serves automotive, electronics, hazardous goods, life sciences, pharmaceutical, temperature controlled, and emergency blood and medical service industries. Its Fleet Solutions division offers fleet management solutions for specific transport and vehicle management needs of various customers. This division also provides various value-added services, such as driver, fuel, and tire management; accident and insurance administration; fleet optimization and route planning; vehicle tracking and recovery; and access to its call center services. In addition, it offers a range of leasing and salary packaging solutions to corporate and government customers, as well as heavy commercial fleet management services. The company's Dealerships division operates 54 motor dealerships in South Africa and 15 motor dealerships in the United Kingdom. This division's motor dealerships offer new and used passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, as well as services, parts, finance, and insurance. The company was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

Bauba Platinum Limited engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral properties in South Africa. The company operates through Chrome Projects and Platinum Exploration segments. It holds interest in the Bauba platinum project comprising eight properties covering an area of approximately 14,390 hectares located in the eastern limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex; and the Bauba platinum chromite mine lying on the Moeijelijk 412KS farm covering an area of approximately 2,271 hectares located in the northeastern limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex in the Limpopo province. The company is based in Bryanston, South Africa. Bauba Platinum Limited is a subsidiary of Highland Trading Investments Limited.

Howden Africa Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, designs, manufactures, and markets specialized air and gas handling solutions worldwide. The company operates through Fans and Heat Exchangers, Environmental Control, and Fabrication Technology segments. The Fans and Heat Exchangers segment focuses on air and gas-cooling technologies within the coal/gold mining and power generation markets. This segment offers boiler fans, heat exchangers, site services, HVAC fans, standard and industrial fans and blowers, main surface fans, auxiliary mine fans, and centrifugal blowers. In addition, this segment is also involved in dust extraction on coal mines, mine cooling and heating, ventilation on demand, engineering, and application engineering activities. The Environmental Control segment offers dust extraction and gas-treatment technologies. This segment's products and services include gas cleaning plants, combustion engineering, furnaces, incinerators, process compressors, refrigeration equipment, water chillers, positive displacement blowers, waste water treatment, and control and instrumentation, as well as mine cooling and heating, engineering solutions, and application engineering. The Fabrication Technology division distributes equipment and filler metals for welding and cutting applications. This segment offers air gouging and exothermic cuttings, gas equipment, welding consumables, welding equipment, plasma cutting and torches, welding automation and robotics, and cutting automation products. It serves power generation, petrochemical, mining, construction, refrigeration, water treatment, machinery, fabrication, ship building, and general industries. The company was founded in 1854 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Howden Africa Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Howden Group South Africa Limited.

South African Coal Mining Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, produces and sells coal products in South Africa. The company has coal mining operations in the Ermelo/Breyten district of the Mpumalanga province of South Africa. It is also involved in the operation of the Umlabu siding, which is situated on the Voorslag property; and equipment leasing activities. The company is headquartered in Breyten, South Africa. South African Coal Mining Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Royal Bafokeng Capital (Pty) Ltd.
companylegalname: South African Coal Mining Holdings Ltd

spbusinessdescription: Buildmax Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the provision of mining services, and equipment sales and rental services primarily in South Africa. The company offers mining, SHECQ management, plant and equipment hire, mine rehabilitation, drill and blast, supply chain, IT and communication, and monitoring systems services to the opencast coal mining sector. It is also involved in the disposal of the second-hand equipment, as well as short-term rental of equipment. Buildmax Limited was founded in 1939 and is headquartered in Benoni, South Africa.

Pick n Pay Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a retailer of food, grocery, and general merchandise. It owns and franchises stores under various formats, including hypermarkets; supermarkets; convenience stores; pharmacies; and liquor, punch, express, hardware, and clothing stores under the Pick n Pay and Boxer names. The company offers various products, such as food, non-edible groceries, clothing, liquor and tobacco, health and beauty products, building and hardware products, and general merchandise. As of February 28, 2016, the company operated 1,410 stores, including 804 company-owned stores and 549 franchise stores; and TM 57 supermarkets. It also provides value-added services, including mobile money, third-party bill payments, gift cards, pre-paid electricity, lotto, and travel and event tickets. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.
Clicks Group Limited engages in the retail of health, beauty, and wellness products in South Africa. The company operates through Retail and Distribution segments.
Woolworths Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates a chain of retail stores in Sub-Saharan Africa, Australia, New Zealand, and internationally.

Eskom Holdings SOC Limited generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to industrial, mining, commercial, agricultural, and residential customers in South Africa. It generates power though nuclear, hydro-electric, wind, gas turbine, coal, and pumped storage plants. The company also operates service concessions for the generation and/or transmission of electricity in Mali and Uganda. In addition, it sells electricity to metros and municipalities who in turn redistribute it to businesses and households within their areas of supply; and purchases electricity from independent power producers, as well as buys and sells electricity in the Southern African Development Community region. The company was formerly known as Eskom Holdings Limited and changed its name to Eskom Holdings SOC Limited in May 2011. Eskom Holdings SOC Limited was founded in 1923 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited, an investment holding company, operates in hotel and leisure, interactive gaming, transport, and mining businesses. It owns and operates hotels and casinos, as well as gaming machines and bingo centers. The company also offers scheduled passenger services through operating 1,073 buses serving 900 routes covering a total area of approximately 2,460 square kilometers; has interests in 3 coal properties; and operates conference and exhibition venues. In addition, it produces and markets wine and brandy; and develops, manufactures, and supplies pressed components for the automotive catalytic converter and OEM markets, as well as provides tubular and exhaust-related components, welding components, poly-V-pulleys, and door lock mechanisms and assemblies. Further, the company provides IT professional services in business analysis and software development; and technology based services and systems for road safety, traffic management, and revenue collection. It has operations in South Africa, Africa, the United Kingdom, and Australia. Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited is based in Zonnebloem, South Africa.

addressline3: Corner of Katherine and West Streets
spbusinessdescription: Randgold & Exploration Company Limited, an investment and exploration company, operates in the gold mining sector in South Africa. It holds the prospecting rights for platinum group metals, nickel, and copper in the Doornbosch project located in the Mpumalanga province.
Trans Hex Group Limited engages in the exploration, mining, and marketing of diamonds from land and marine alluvial deposits in South Africa and Angola.

Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited publishes and prints books, magazines, newspapers, and commercial print primarily in the Republic of South Africa. It is involved in publishing various community newspapers, The Citizen daily newspaper, and other magazines. The company operates online digital platforms, including AutoDealer, DealFinder, Money Web, Look Local, and Property Week, as well as a community news; and provides digital, as well as sales, advertising, and marketing services. It also offers printed packaging solutions, such as litho printed folding cartons, gravure printed cigarette packs and display cartons, litho and gravure printed wet glue, and pressure sensitive labels for the beer and beverage industries, as well as various forms of flexible packaging and specialized printing solutions for the point of sale and entertainment industries. In addition, the company manufactures, imports, and markets printing inks, as well as exports newspaper inks to Tanzania and Uganda; and provides digital, gravure, sheet-fed offset, and web offset printing services. Further, it manufactures and distributes stationery products; replicates and distributes CDs and DVDs; provides repro design services; owns properties; and distributes magazines. Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa.

spbusinessdescription: Sanlam Limited provides various financial solutions to individual, business, and institutional clients. The company operates through Sanlam Personal Finance, Sanlam Emerging Markets, Sanlam Investments, Santam, and Sanlam Corporate segments.

Truworths International Limited, an investment holding and management company, engages in the retail of fashion apparel and accessories primarily in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Germany, the Republic of Ireland, Namibia, Swaziland, Botswana, and other African countries. The company operates through Truworths and Office segments. It offers bottoms, tops, knitwear, skirts and dresses, jackets and coats, and shoes and bags; sweats and formalwear; and accessories and fragrances for women, men, newborn, girls, and boys under the Truworths, Earthaddict, LTD, Daniel Hechter, Inwear, Ginger Mary, Zeta, Truworths Man, UZZI, Naartjie, and Earthchild brand names. The company operates approximately 650 stores in South Africa; and 40 stores in the rest of Africa. Truworths International Ltd was founded in 1917 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Aveng Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primary engages in the construction and engineering, mining, and steel business worldwide. The company operates through Construction and Engineering, Mining, and Manufacturing and Processing segments. It offers a range of integrated services that cover building, civil engineering, roads, earthworks, concrete, ground engineering, mechanical, piping, electrical, and instrumentation contracting. The company also operates as an engineering, construction, building, and maintenance contractor for the building, infrastructure, and resource markets focusing on building, rail, civil, electrical, marine, mechanical pipelines, fabrication, tunneling, and underground services. In addition, it provides mining services in the areas of shaft sinking, underground development and contract mining, opencast mining, mineral processing, acid mine drainage plants, construction of mining related infrastructure, and supply of mining equipment and products. Further, the company manufactures and supplies concrete products to the construction sector; services and engineered solutions to mining, water, oil and gas, and construction clients; and rail construction and maintenance services to the transport sector, as well as supplies various products and services to the construction, mining, and automotive industries. Aveng Limited is based in Boksburg, South Africa.

Comair Limited provides scheduled and non-scheduled airline services in South Africa, sub-Saharan Africa, and the Indian Ocean Islands. It operates through two segments, Airline and Non-airline. The company operates scheduled airline services under the kulula and British Airways brands. It also offers travel and holiday packaging services; and operates airport lounges. In addition, the company provides a range of aviation-related ground school subjects and flight simulator training for a range of Boeing 737 type aircraft, as well as ancillary subjects, and cabin crew and flight dispatcher training services. Further, it operates travel agency business; and owns various properties. The company operates a fleet of 25 aircraft. Comair Limited was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Peregrine Holdings Limited provides various financial products and services to individuals and institutions in South Africa and internationally. The company provides wealth management, asset management, broking and structuring, corporate finance advisory, and proprietary investment services. It also provides trust, foreign exchange, treasury management, single manager hedge funds, property investments, and investment related services, as well as distribution and consulting services related to derivative solutions. Peregrine Holdings Limited was founded in 1996 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

African Dawn Capital Limited, a micro finance company, provides various financial products in South Africa. It operates through Investment Advisory and Investment Management, Micro finance, and Rentals of Properties in Possession segments. The company specializes in micro finance, debtor discounting, and structured property finance. It offers investment advisory and investment management services to entrepreneurial and innovative companies; and micro finance services primarily to individuals. The company also rents a residential complex with 76 units. African Dawn Capital Limited was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa.

ADvTECH Limited provides education, training, and staff placement services in the Republic of South Africa. It operates in three divisions: Schools, Tertiary, and Resourcing. The Schools division provides pre-primary, primary, and secondary education services. The Tertiary division offers education on diploma, degree, and postgraduate levels. The Resourcing division provides permanent, temporary, and contract staffing solutions in the areas of network engineering, network finance, network information technology (IT) recruitment, accounting and finance, office support, engineering, IT, supply chain/freight, and information communication technology, as well as provides recruitment advertising services. The company is based in Sandton, the Republic of South Africa.

AH-Vest Limited manufactures and sells food related products in South Africa. It offers tomato sauce and other value added products to the catering and hotel industries. The company was founded in 1988 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Datacentrix Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides ICT systems and solutions to enterprises in South Africa. The company operates through three divisions: Managed Services, Business Applications, and Technology Solutions. The Managed Services division offers service aggregation, service desk, managed systems, managed networks, managed entry point, monitoring, hosting, co-location, managed print and document, security operations center, and electronic fraud management; cloud services; and managed talent solutions. The Business Applications division provides analytics and business intelligence, enterprise information management, and enterprise resource planning solutions to automate and streamline business processes, enhance productivity, and ensure decisions by management. The Technology Solutions division is involved in the procurement, installation, management, and maintenance of customer server environments through server platform technology; and configuration, management, monitoring, and control of distributed enterprise systems. This division also offers data center, data storage, information security, networking and unified communications, end user computing, logistics, and eLearning solutions. The company is based in Midrand, South Africa. Datacentrix Holdings Limiteds a subsidiary of DCT Holdings Pty Limited.

Purple Group Limited, a financial services company, engages in trading and asset management businesses in the Republic of South Africa and internationally. The company operates EasyEquities, an online investment platform that offers access to buy shares, baskets of shares, exchange traded funds, or other listed JSE products; and GT247.com, an online trading platform, which provides access to various markets through contracts for differences and futures. It also provides private broking services; and asset management services, such as segregated portfolios, unit trusts, and hedge funds. The company was formerly known as Purple Capital Limited and changed its name to Purple Group Limited in December 2013. Purple Group Limited is based in Hyde Park, the Republic of South Africa.

DigiCore Holdings Limited designs, researches, develops, manufactures, sells, and supports GPS/GSM fleet management and vehicle tracking solutions primarily in South Africa and internationally. It provides various vehicle tracking solutions, including Ctrack Insure, a monitoring and tracking system that offers proactive alerts in the event of battery or tracking-unit tamper or border approach; Ctrack Insure Protector for tracking and monitoring with smart collision and security; Ctrack Secure, which provides Internet-enabled access to view vehicle movements; and Ctrack Secure Protector, a satellite vehicle tracking solution. The company also provides fleet management solutions, such as Ctrack Lite, an entry level vehicle tracking and fleet management system providing driver behavior information and full status reports, such as over speeding, harsh braking, and excessive idling; Ctrack Assist for the tracking and management of light commercial, sales, FML, car rental, and security vehicles, as well as trailer fleets; OBDII Fuel Reader, which provides fuel economy data assisting small and large fleet operators to manage fuel related costs; Ctrack Solo, a mobile solution for the tracking and management of the professional hauler, logistics and supply chain management, mobile workforce management, public transport, and emergency services applications; Ctrack On-the-Road, an onboard system that helps fleet operators in saving time and money through advanced navigation, task management, messaging, optimal routing, voice functionality, and driver behavior; and Ctrack Multi-comms. In addition, it offers Ctrack Wireless, a re-deployable tracking system. The company provides its products for private vehicles and small fleet, medium to large fleet, heavy duty, and transport, as well as asset tracking, monitoring, and revenue management. DigiCore Holdings Limited was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

Astrapak Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and distributes various plastic packaging products primarily in South Africa. The company offers plain and printed jars, closures, and tubes for the personal care market; closures and bottles for the homecare market; roll-on balls, deodorant bottles, multi-polymer containers, and closures for various applications; containers for lubricant and petrochemical applications; and personal care and pharmaceutical grade components, as well as trays and cups. It also provides thin walled injection-moulded tubs, containers, lids, and cups for dairy applications; packaging products for bakery and deli applications, as well as a range of trays for MAP applications and shelf life extension; and a range of thermoformed pots, food containers, and drinking cups. The company is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Discovery Limited provides various insurance products. The company offers health, life, car and vehicle, home, boat, and personal liability insurance products. It also provides investment products and credit cards; and Vitality, a wellness program that offers rewards for getting healthier. The company was formerly known as Discovery Holdings Limited and changed its name to Discovery Limited in December 2012. Discovery Limited was founded in 1992 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

addressline2: Green Hill Village Office Park, on Lynnwood Road
spbusinessdescription: Ecsponent Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in capital raising, asset management, enterprise/SME funding, collections, and private equity businesses in South Africa, Botswana, Zambia, Namibia, and Swaziland. It operates through Financial Services, Private Equity, Collections, and Corporate segments. The company offers financing to niche markets, such as employee benefits and SME funding, as well as houses investment products offered to the retail markets. It also invests in biotechnology, property development, and other businesses; and provides collection agency services, including tracing defaulters, repayment and contract agreement, debit order and related collection management, and legal pursuance. The company was formerly known as John Daniel Holdings Limited. Ecsponent Limited was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Pretoria East, South Africa.
Brimstone Investment Corporation Limited engages financial services, healthcare, and industrial and enterprise development businesses. The company is based in Newlands, the Republic of South Africa.

PSV Holdings Ltd provides steel, stainless steel, industrial supplies, specialised control valves, engineering linings, cryogenic equipment, storage tanks, and technology to the mining, water, waste water management, health care, infrastructure, and manufacturing sectors.  The company operates through two segments, Industrial Supplies and Specialised Services. The Industrial Supplies segment purchases and distributes general industrial and automotive supplies; supplies steel, piping, industrial tools, consumable supplies, and automotive capital equipment to mining and industrial clients; offers bespoke and turnkey solutions to companies in need of computerized vehicle testing stations and general workshop equipment; and provides consultancy services on workshop requirements, as well as offers one-stop solution for mining projects. The Specialised Services segment is involved in the manufacture and supply of gas and cryogenic equipment, including road tankers and cryogenic storage vessels to gas and chemical industries; supply of geosynthetic and plastic lining solutions to assist mining operators for the purpose of seepage containment, corrosion, and environmental protection; and the provision of repair and refurbishment services. PSV Holdings Limited is based in Greenstone Hill, South Africa.

EOH Holdings Limited provides consulting, technology, and outsourcing solutions in South Africa, Africa, and the United Kingdom. The company offers consulting services comprising strategy and operations, information management and analytics, information risk management, process improvement, people change management, program and project management, PMOs, ICT architecture and optimization, and digital services. It also provides technology services, including enterprise applications, information analytics and big data, information risk management, IT management and optimization, software development and integration, digital, and industrial technologies. In addition, the company offers outsourcing services that consist of transformational outsourcing, managed, and cloud services, as well as business process outsourcing and human capital services. It primarily serves various industries, such as financial services, telecommunications, manufacturing and logistics, public sector, mining, and retail. EOH Holdings Limited is headquartered in Bedfordview, South Africa.

Verimark Holdings Limited operates as a retail company that sources, develops, and distributes various products in the housewares, exercise and fitness, health and beauty, DIY, automotive, educational toys, and personal comfort categories in South Africa and internationally. The company offers houseware products comprising slicers and choppers; blade sharpeners, power peelers, rolling knives, and kitchen tools; houseware solutions; and cooking products, as well as accessories and general houseware products. It also provides health and beauty products that include appliances and beauty products; cookware products, such as combos and sets, pans, and lids; and cleaning products comprising mops and brooms, microfiber cloths, replacements, accessories, window mates, and detergents, as well as cleaning solutions. In addition, the company offers DIY products, which include sealants, garden hoses, motion sensor lights, screwdrivers, and blade sharpeners, as well as pool surface skimming systems and replacement bags, and renovator sets and spanners; car care products; educational toys, game stations, and other toys; and fitness products, such as home work out and ab sculpting systems. It primarily distributes cookware and kitchenware products under the Bauer, Bastille, Twista, and Shogun; home cleaning products under the Genesis, Floorwiz, and Microwiz; health and fitness products under the Maxxus, Orbitrek, and V-ssage; DIY and automotive products under the Diamond Guard, Prolong, Durablade, Pool Gobbler, and Gorilla; and beauty products under the Perfect Curl, Pink Armor, and Genie Bra brands, as well as educational and fun toys under the i-Play brand. The company sells its products through approximately 1,401 retail partner stores, as well as 77 owned and franchised stores under the As Seen on TV name; and through online. Verimark Holdings Limited was founded in 1977 and is headquartered in Randburg, South Africa.

addressline4: Corner 14th Avenue and Hendrik Potgieter Road
spbusinessdescription: Indequity Group Limited provides short-term insurance products to professional and affluent private client markets in South Africa. The company offers Uniq-Cover, a short-term insurance for individuals that offers cover for buildings, household contents, vehicles, and all risks. It also provides Probiz, a short term insurance policy for professional businesses covering buildings, office contents, electronic equipment, business all risks, vehicles, and business interruption. The company is based in Constantia Kloof, South Africa.

Adapt IT Holdings Limited provides specialized information technology (IT) services and solutions. The company's Education segment provides turnkey enterprise resource planning (ERP) product, ITS integrator, and services to the higher education sector. Its Manufacturing segment offers tranquility ERP; safety health environment and quality solutions; SAP human capital management cloud services; and telecommunications business intelligence solutions. The company's Financial Services segment provides business intelligence solutions and services to the financial services sector. Its Energy segment offers consulting and software solutions and services to oil and gas, power, renewable, and other energy sectors. The company also provides software services in the areas of business and technical advisory, cloud computing, development and integration, recruitment, and training and development, as well as offers application development services. It serves the mining and manufacturing, education, financial services, and energy sectors in approximately 38 countries worldwide. Adapt IT Holdings Limited has partnerships with IBM, Microsoft, Oracle, and SAP. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

addressline2: Corner Bram Fischer Drive and Will Scarlet Road
spbusinessdescription: Cognition Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides interactive telecommunication, switching, and business services primarily in South Africa. The company operates through two segments, Active Data Exchange Services, and Knowledge Creation and Management. The company's active data exchange services include short message, interactive voice response, Vmail one-on-one marketing, mobi site, fulfillment, call center, and bespoke services, as well as unstructured supplementary service data, instant messaging, email, fax2email, and email2fax services. Its active data exchange services also comprise advertising, promotion, direct marketing, and CRM services. In addition, the company provides Knowledge 350, a 15 step business process, which creates an integrated and logical process that assists companies to build databases and to move from segmenting customers to single customer profiles with detailed demographics and psychographics. Further, it offers MyPoint, a managed community service, which enables panelists to complete surveys and reward them with points, prizes, and benefits; Community Builds, an interactive relationship-building program; qualitative and quantitative market research services; and omnibus/syndicated studies. Additionally, the company provides Web design, development, and hosting services, as well as associated search engine optimization input services; and annual quantifications, reports tracking, in-store observation, and liquor in-store pricing, as well as print ad tracking, and commissioned and consumer research services. It serves apparel, automotive, consumer packaged goods, financial, food services, information technology and communication, manufacturing, packaging, raw materials, retail, and wholesale sectors and industries. The company was formerly known as FoneWorx Holdings Limited and changed its name to Cognition Holdings Limited in January 2015. Cognition Holdings Limited is headquartered in Randburg, South Africa.

MICROmega Holdings Limited provides information technology, financial, and support services in South Africa. It offers occupational health, safety, and environmental risk management services; and contractual manpower, recruitment, HR and industrial relations management, payroll bureau, project logistics, and employee benefits for mining, engineering, construction, offshore oil and gas, petrochemical, power generation, and agriculture sectors. The company also provides intermediary broking services in the areas of foreign exchange, OTC derivatives, fixed income securities, repurchase agreements, and money market instruments to commercial and investment banks, stock brokers, and trading entities. In addition, it offers integrated technology solutions, enterprise management systems, and multidisciplinary professional services, including accounting, auditing, and risk management; corporate and municipal finance; change and HR management; engineering; information communication technology infrastructure design, configuration, implementation, and maintenance; software and systems development; administration; project management; organizational restructuring; and strategic planning to municipalities, public entities, government, and private sector. Further, the company offers plastic water meters, ball valves, and meter boxes; pre-payment water meters and electronic water control devices; and consulting services. Additionally, it provides multi-protocol label switching networks, hosting facilities, Internet, and cloud computing services; Set-it, a system to design, integrate, and manage organizational strategy; iConnect, a wireless alarming solution; Whatsup plug and play solution; Coretalk, a SMS communication service; and PROMU accounting package. It also provides chemical analytical services that focus on chemical analysis of food, fish, and beverage products. The company is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. The company is a subsidiary of Friedshelf 1382 (Pty) Ltd.

Massmart Holdings Limited operates as a retail and wholesale distributor. It operates through four segment: Massdiscounters, Masswarehouse, Massbuild, and Masscash. The Massdiscounters segment operates discount retail stores that offer general merchandise, fresh food, groceries, liquor, and footwear, as well as technological solutions in multimedia and hi-tech under the Game and DionWired retail formats. This segment operates 165 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Ghana, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia. The Masswarehouse segment operates warehouse stores under the Makro and The Fruitspot names that sell food, liquor, and general merchandise for personal, commercial, and trading customers; and fresh and cut fruit and vegetables. This segment operates 20 stores in South Africa. The Massbuild segment operates DIY, home improvement, and building materials stores under the Builders Warehouse, Builders Express, Builders Superstore, and Builders Trade Depot brands. This segment operates 104 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, and Zambia. The Masscash segment engages in the wholesale of food, liquor, cosmetics, toiletries, and haircare products under the CBW and Trident, Jumbo, and Shield brands; and operation of retail outlets under Cambridge Food and Rhino brands. This segment operates 123 stores South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Mozambique, Namibia, and Swaziland. Massmart Holdings Limited was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Massmart Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Main Street 830 (Pty) Ltd.

Mercantile Bank Holdings Limited, a bank-controlling and investment holding company, provides banking and financial services to the business, commercial, and alliance banking markets in South Africa. The company's deposit products include call accounts, notice deposits, fixed deposits, money market accounts, and business savings accounts; and lending products comprise overdrafts, term loans, asset finance, and commercial property finance. It also provides debit cards, credit cards, drive cards, and electronic banking services; travel insurance, and short and long-term insurance solutions; and cash and merchant services. In addition, the company offers spot market services, foreign exchange contracts, and derivatives, as well as traveller's cheque and foreign cash services; money market solutions, including call accounts, term deposits, and structured solutions; and trade finance products, such as letters of credit, trade guarantees, bills for collection, and exchange control and SWIFT products, as well as private banking services. Further, it is involved in securitization, property holding, and rental finance activities. The company was founded in 1965 and is headquartered in Sandown, South Africa. Mercantile Bank Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Caixa Geral de Depositos S.A.

Santova Limited provides international logistics solutions primarily in Africa, the Asia Pacific, the United Kingdom, and Europe. The company offers supply chain solutions; multimodal shipping solutions, including customs and excise clearing and consultancy, freight forwarding, liner agency, groupage and consolidations, warehousing and distribution, ex-works and destination value add services, and chartering by sea, air, road, and rail; consultations and pre-emptive planning, organizing, controlling, and monitoring services for the projects; and sourcing and procurement management services. It also provides software packages and intelligent management information systems that offer a delivery network to individuals, shippers, and companies; domestic, marine, and structured specialist once-off insurance products; and information technology services. Santova Limited is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

Moneyweb Holdings Limited, an integrated media company, engages in the digital, broadcast, and print publishing fields in the Republic of South Africa. The company provides online investment information through its flagship Internet brand, Moneyweb.co.za; and operates mineweb.com, an international mining portal. It also supplies business news to various SABC radio stations, including SAfm, RSG, and Lotus FM; publishes CitiBusiness, the business supplement of Citizen newspaper; and offers advertising services on its platforms. The company is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Moneyweb Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited.

OneLogix Group Limited provides logistics and related services in South Africa. The company operates through Abnormal Logistics and Primary Products Logistics segments. It offers vehicle delivery services through a fleet of approximately 300 trucks and specialized car carrying trailers; new commercial vehicle delivery services; and project logistics and abnormal load solutions, including scheduling and executing harbor movements, and warehousing and management of staged and aggregate moves with monitoring and reporting services. The company also provides liquid transport services for agricultural, chemical, foodgrade, cryogenic, or liquid petroleum gas products through a fleet of approximately 160 tankers; cross-border movement services for general freight and commodities; refrigerated logistics services for chilled, fruit, and vegetable markets; and transportation services for agricultural inputs, such as fertilizer, as well as the final agricultural products. In addition, it provides accident repairs, structural repairs to chassis, cab rebuilds, specialized spray painting, and accident recovery services for commercial trucks; warehouse handling and storage services; specialized transport related accounting software solutions; and integrated driver management solutions. OneLogix Group Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Primeserv Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides human capital solutions in the Republic of South Africa. The company operates in two segments, Staffing and Recruitment Services, and Training and Consulting Services. It offers human resources (HR) solutions, such as business and HR strategy and structure workshops, HR balanced scorecards, business and job profiles or internal capacity building, integrated functional/divisional and/or job profiles development, competency and psychometric assessment, learning and development strategy development, skills audits and/or training needs analysis, learning and development interventions implementation, ETQA processes, and learning materials design and development. The company's HR solutions also comprise performance management audits, methodology workshops, policies and procedures, and training; measurement tools development; job evaluation/grading; remuneration and reward systems and processes; salary surveys; HR policies and procedures; climate surveys; IR consulting and training; occupational health and safety consulting and training; and BEE consulting support services. In addition, it provides flexible staffing, permanent staff resourcing, payroll and wage bureau, corporate and technical training, learnership, specialist recruitment, and talent management services, as well as employee lifestyle benefit related products. The company serves logistics, warehousing and distribution, wholesale and retail, manufacturing and engineering, and construction sectors. Primeserv Group Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Illovo, the Republic of South Africa.

Adrenna Property Group Limited invests in properties. The company operates through Investment Property Holdings, Property-Related Services, and Property Sales segments. Adrenna Property Group Limited is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

ISA Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides network, Internet, and information security solutions to the sub-Saharan African market. The company offers a range of managed security services comprising MSS assist service, which provides the customer with telephonic and e-mail access to IT security specialists; MSS access service for gaining secure remote access in the security systems; MSS monitor service, a monitoring service; and MSS manage service that provides administrative, maintenance, and security infrastructure management functions for the clients. It also provides training services for IT professionals. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

African Equity Empowerment Investments Limited formerly known as Sekunjalo Investments Limited is a private equity firm specializing in acquisitions, PIPEs, and buyouts. It seeks to invest in companies operating in the food, fishing, marine, biotherapeutics , healthcare, pharmaceuticals, information technology, telecommunication, Mobile solutions, solar energy, financial services, aquaculture, biotechnology, enterprise development, events management including entertainment, and travel sectors. The firm prefers to invest companies based in South Africa. It is open to acquiring non-controlling stakes. The firm invests using its balance sheet and personal capital. African Equity Empowerment Investments Limited was founded in May 1996 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Spur Corporation Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a restaurant franchisor in South Africa and internationally. The company operates and franchises sit-down family restaurants under the Spur Steak Ranches, including Spur Grill & Go, as well as Panarottis Pizza Pasta, and John Dory's Fish Grill Sushi brands; quick-service takeaways under the Captain DoRegos brand; steakhouses under the The Hussar Grill brand; Italian pizza and pasta restaurants under the Casa Bella brand; and gourmet burgers, ribs, and wings restaurants under the RocoMamas brand. It operates through a network of 575 outlets in Africa, Mauritius, and Australia. In addition, the company engages in the sauce manufacturing, warehousing and product distribution, decor manufacturing, export, radio station, training, and call center businesses. Spur Corporation Limited was founded in 1967 and is headquartered in Century City, South Africa.

SilverBridge Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides business solutions to the financial services industry. It operates through Implementation Services, Support services, Hosting and outsourcing Services, Software Rental, and Research and Development segments. The company's product include ExergyLife, a policy administration system for the life insurance companies; ExergyGroups, a group scheme administration system; and Snapper, a Microsoft Word style user interface that allows the creation of standard letters. It also offers, rents, and leases Eco-Suite, an end-to-end solution for life assurance, pension, and group administration. In addition, the company provides hosting, technical outsourcing, and business process outsourcing services; actuarial consulting, including fraud investigations, product development, pricing and ratings, enterprise risk management, corporate planning, and others; and business intelligence solutions comprising valuation extracts, basic business indicators, and business intelligence solutions, as well as data analytics services. SilverBridge Holdings Limited offers its products in the Republic of South Africa, as well as in other African countries, including Swaziland, Zimbabwe, Namibia, Lesotho, Kenya, Angola, Botswana, Malawi, Mauritius, and Ghana. The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Pretoria, the Republic of South Africa.

Amalgamated Electronic Corporation Limited, through its subsidiaries, designs, manufactures, and supplies electronic equipment, technologies, and solutions to the security and power supply industries in South Africa and internationally. The company operates data network comprising base stations and repeater technology for the wireless transmission of data across secure network channels. It also designs radio and GSM transmitters, receivers, and transceivers used primarily in the security industry and related niche markets; and a range of related electronic security products, which include security personnel monitoring units, vehicle dispatchers, long and short range remote controllers, and electronic gate opening technology. In addition, the company is involved in the property investment business; and provision of financial and administration services, as well as installs, manages, and maintains various equipment and licenses used on radio and GSM Independent Communications Authority of South Africa frequencies. Amalgamated Electronic Corporation Limited is based in Florida, South Africa. As of October 21, 2016, Amalgamated Electronics Corporation Limited was taken private.

Value Group Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides supply chain solutions primarily in South Africa. It operates through General Distribution, and Truck Rental and Other segments. The company offers supply chain solutions, including door-to-door offerings, distribution and warehousing of hazardous cargo, courier services, warehousing facilities, and distribution services to customers in automotive, fast moving consumer goods, electronics, chemical, textile, packaging, mining, construction, telecommunications, and pharmaceutical industries. It also provides fleet management, forklift and commercial vehicle rental and leasing, clearing and forwarding services, and container handling services. In addition, the company offers repairs and maintenance, materials handling, and import and export services. Value Group Limited was founded in 1981 and is headquartered in Isando, South Africa.

Stellar Capital Partners Limited is no longer investing. It is a principal investment firm specializing in investments in a portfolio of equity, debt and hybrid securities, in listed and unlisted businesses, unconstrained by any particular market or sector. The firm also seeks to invest in growth and early-maturity stage businesses in which management teams remain equity incentivised throughout the investment life cycle. It prefers to invest in financial services, technology sector, industrials and support services, financials and disruptive opportunities across all markets. The firm seeks to invest in companies based in South Africa with focused international operations with the ability to over time invest in foreign based investments also. It prefers to take strategic or controlling interests in its portfolio companies, establishing primarily large minority equity holdings, but retain the ability to hold majority holdings, particularly during the initial stage of the investment. The firm seeks board representation within its investees' reporting structures without establishing board control for prolonged periods of the investment cycle. The firm prefers not to retain operational management of its investees for prolonged periods, but will hold the ability do so during the initial stage of the investment or as is deemed necessary. The firm seeks to opportunistically utilise its balance sheet to generate fees for shareholders through corporate finance strategies in support of investee companies or on a standalone basis. It was formerly known as ConvergeNet Holdings Limited. Stellar Capital Partners Limited was founded in 2005 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa with an additional office in Centurion, South Africa.

Winhold Limited, an investment holding company, manufactures and distributes polyethylene and polypropeylene bags, and sheeting and packaging products to the agricultural, chemical, construction, food processing, industrial, and consumer markets in South Africa. It operates through Flexible Packaging, Flexible Construction, Trading, and Property & Group segments. The company also supplies capital and consumer goods to the mining, petrochemical, and general industries; and manufactures and distributes pallets and other products made out of recycled polyethylene terephthalate polymer bottles. In addition, it offers extruded flexible sheeting for agricultural and construction markets. Winhold Limited was incorporated in 1945 and is headquartered in Germiston, South Africa.

Remgro Limited is a principal investment firm. The firm prefers to invest in financial services, food, liquor and home care, banking, insurance, industrial, healthcare, infrastructure, information technology infrastructure services, media, and sport. It considers investments in South African investments and other African and international countries though investee companies. The firm typically invests in companies with significant influence and board representation. It mainly focuses on the provision of support rather than on being involved in the day-to-day management of business units of investees. Remgro Limited was founded in 1948 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Astral Foods Limited operates as an integrated poultry producer in South Africa and internationally. It operates through three segments: Poultry, Feed, and Other Africa. The company manufactures animal feeds and broiler genetics; produces and sells day-old broiler chicks and hatching eggs; manufactures and markets vitamin and mineral pre-mixes for use in animal feeds; and offers a range of feed additives, and commodity and specialty raw materials. It is also involved in the integrated breeder and broiler production operations; operation of abattoirs; processing operations; and sale and distribution of various poultry brands. In addition, the company retails animal health products; and provides laboratory analytical services to the animal feed industry. The company offers its products under the Ross 308, Meadow, Provimi, National Chicks, CAL, Goldi, County Fair, Festive, Mountain Valley, SupaStar, TigerChicks, Tiger Animal Feeds, Mozpintos, and National Chicks Swaziland brands. Astral Foods Limited is based in Centurion, South Africa.

StratCorp Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the provision of financial products, health and wellness products, and general financing primarily in South Africa. The company offers natural health and lifestyle products under the I-Cura brand; and develops residential properties in the middle market segment. It provides investment products; insurance products, such as death, disability, hospitalization, retrenchment, and funeral insurance; and rental finance, finance agreements, or loan facilities. The company was founded in 2000 and is based in Centurion, South Africa. StratCorp Limited is a subsidiary of Stratcorp Empowerment Holdings Ltd.

African and Overseas Enterprises Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in retail trading and property businesses. It is involved in retailing clothing and fashion accessories in South Africa, as well as in franchising retail stores in Kenya and Namibia. It also engages in the property investment activities. African and Overseas Enterprises Limited is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Beige Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the contract and packaging manufacturing of household cleaning, personal care and toiletry, herbal, homeopathic, and pharmaceutical products. It operates through two segments, Outsource Manufacturing and Packaging. The company offers homecare products, including laundry powders and liquids, laundry bars, bleach, dishwashing liquids, oven and kitchen cleaners, household cleaners, disinfectants, and room sprays; and face, hands and nail, body, hair, legs and feet, oral, baby, and ethnic hair care products, as well as bath and shower products, soaps, cosmetics, and men's grooming products. It also manufactures herbal, homeopathic, and pharmaceutical products, such as tinctures, powders, liquids, tablets, capsules, and vitamins and food supplements. In addition, the company provides packaging products for chemical, industrial, personal care, and food and beverage markets. The company is based in Kempton Park, South Africa. Beige Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of The Lion Match Company (Pty) Limited.

Phumelela Gaming and Leisure Limited operates as a horseracing and totalizator betting company in South Africa and internationally. It operates and manages 4 racecourses, 5 training centers, approximately 200 tote outlets, a telephone-betting center, and an online tote betting site. The company also operates Tellytrack, a horseracing television channel that broadcasts live horseracing audio, visual, and data to retail outlets and home viewers. In addition, it produces various horseracing publications, including Computaform, a horseracing form guide; Racing Express, a horseracing insert that appears in daily newspaper; and Computaform Express, a multi-meeting horseracing form guide, as well as operates horseracing venue as a banqueting and conferencing venue. Further, it offers sports betting services through various channels, including a range of tote bets; and engages in property holding activities. The company was founded in 1997 and is based in Turffontein, South Africa.

Coronation Fund Managers Limited is a publicly owned investment manager. The firm provides its services to pension and provident funds, medical schemes, unit trusts, banks, insurers and other fund managers, international retirement funds, endowments and family offices. It launches and manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. Coronation Fund Managers Limited was founded in 1993 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Investec Bank Limited operates as a specialist bank in Southern Africa. The company's banking products and services include private bank accounts, private business accounts, fixed deposits, instant access accounts, and flexible notice accounts. Its financing and lending products comprise motor vehicle finance, home and personal loans, asset finance, specialized and structured finance, property development finance, aviation finance, corporate lending, asset finance, growth and acquisition finance, commercial property finance, and medical practice and specialized finance. The company also offers investing solutions, such as portfolio and wealth management services, offshore investing services, asset management services, structured products, and advisory and online stock broking services, as well as institutional, property fund, charities and trusts, business cash, and deposits and cash management solutions. In addition, it provides foreign exchange services; and equity services, including forex, interest rate, money market, commodity, equities structuring, and institutional equity trading services. Further, the company offers property development, acquisitions, and fund management services; and power and infrastructure, and commodities and resources finance, as well as medical banking, young professional banking, and online banking services. It serves corporates, government, and institutional clients, as well as high net worth individuals, entrepreneurs, high-income professionals, self-employed entrepreneurs, owner managers in mid-market companies, and investors. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Bank Limited operates as a subsidiary of Investec Limited.

Nedbank Limited provides various banking and financial services to various customers. The company accepts various deposit products, including current accounts, savings accounts, call and notice deposits, fixed deposits, negotiable certificates of deposits, term deposits, and cash management deposits, as well as investment accounts. It also provides credit cards; home, vehicle, student, and personal loans; overdrafts; financial planning services; and foreign exchange services. In addition, the company offers assets, life, income and credit protection, and funeral insurance; and general business, specialized, general liability, business overheads, business owner, and key person insurance, as well as direct business cover, investment services, and capital guarantees. Further, it provides a mix of listed offshore equity portfolios; investment plans; portfolio management services; corporate finance, stock broking, trading, debt advisory, and management services; start-up, business growth, and short term loans, as well as structured, property finance, and asset finance solutions; financial assistance and debtor management solutions; and aircraft, carbon, export credit, global commodity, leveraged, mining, oil and gas, private equity, property, public sector, infrastructure, energy, and telecomm finance, as well as corporate lending and advances. Additionally, the company offers payment and receipts, documentary credits and collections, guarantees, trade finance, customer foreign currency accounts, and treasury services; cash management, electronic banking, trade, and custodial services; and merchant payment and support solutions. It operates in South Africa, other African countries, Europe, Asia, the United States, and internationally. The company is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Nedbank Limited is a subsidiary of Nedbank Group Ltd.

Redefine Properties Limited is a privately owned investment manager. The firm engages in investment, ownership, redevelopment, and refurbishment of office, retail, and industrial property. It invests in the real estate and public equity markets across the globe with a focus on South Africa. It also invests in other listed securities of companies operating in the real estate sector. Redefine Properties Limited was founded in 1999 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa with an additional office in Cape Town, South Africa.

The SPAR Group Ltd engages in the wholesale and distribution of goods and services to retail stores in Southern Africa, Switzerland, Ireland, and South West. The company offers a range of groceries and general merchandise, including fresh produce, in-store bakery, butchery, deli, ready-to-eat and home-meal replacements, as well as meat and baked goods; liquor products; building and hardware products; and medicinal and health-related products. It operates six distribution centers and one Build it distribution center, which primarily serves independent retailers that operate SPAR, SUPERSPAR, and KWIKSPAR grocery stores; Build it builders' merchandise outlets; TOPS at SPAR liquor stores; Pharmacy at SPAR pharmacies; SaveMor stores; and other group retail outlets. The SPAR Group Ltd is based in Pinetown, South Africa.

Lewis Group Limited, a credit retailer, sells household furniture and electrical appliances in South Africa and internationally. The company's stores offer household furniture, electrical appliances, home electronics, sound and vision equipment, and furniture to the middle to lower income market under the Lewis, Best Home and Electric, and Beares brand names. It also provides short-term insurance to customers purchasing merchandise on credit. As of March 31, 2016, the company operated 526 Lewis; 127 Best Home and Electric; and 107 Beares stores. Lewis Group Limited was founded in 1934 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Vukile Property Fund Limited operates as a property holding and investment company in South Africa. Its portfolio includes retail, office, and industrial properties. As of March 31, 2012, the company's property portfolio consisted of 72 properties with a gross lettable area of 922,221 square meters. It also provides asset management services in respect of long-term commercial investment property portfolio. Vukile Property Fund Limited is based in Constantia Kloof, South Africa.

Chrometco Limited engages in the exploration and mining of chrome and platinum group metals in South Africa. The company holds interest in Rooderand 46JQ and Portion 2, which cover 1069.1904 hectares of area located in the North West Province in South Africa. Chrometco Limited was founded in 2003 and is based in Highveld Park, South Africa.

Wesizwe Platinum Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration and development of mineral properties in South Africa. The company primarily explores for platinum, palladium, rhodium, and gold. Its flagship project is the Bakubung Platinum Mine located on the Western Limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex in the North West province of South Africa. Wesizwe Platinum Limited was incorporated in 2003 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Esor Limited operates as a civil engineering and construction company in principally South Africa and Zimbabwe. The company operates in two segments, Esor Construction and Esor Developments. It engages in the roads, township infrastructures, water and sewerage reticulation projects, and concrete projects construction, as well as the construction and rehabilitation of onshore pipelines. The company also undertakes building and housing projects, including office, retail, leisure, residential, mining, governmental, and infrastructure projects, as well as undertakes low-income housing projects in bonded and social rental, gap, FLISP, and RDP/BNG markets. In addition, it undertakes environmental and safety, pipeline installation, lining and coating, earthworks, structures, testing and pigging, and valves and other special works; and provides pipe services, such as bridge jacking, culvert jacking, pipejacking, shaft sinking, and slabjacking. Further, the company offers sanitation services, including water and sanitation implementation, bulk water and sewer infrastructure construction, containerized ablution facilities installation, brick and mortar ablution blocks construction, modular ablution facilities construction, septic tank and soak-away pits construction, social facilitation and education. Additionally, it engages in property investment and development activities. The company was formerly known as Esorfranki Limited and changed its name to Esor Limited in December 2013. Esor Limited was founded in 1946 and is based in Germiston, South Africa. As of February 24, 2017, Esor Limited operates as a subsidiary of Geomer Investments Proprietary Limited.

Hospitality Property Fund Limited, a property loan stock company, invests in hotel and leisure properties in South Africa. As of June 30, 2007, it had interests in 21 hotel and resort properties principally located in Gauteng, Western Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, Eastern Cape, and Mpumalanga. The company is based in Sandton, South Africa.

JSE Limited operates as a securities exchange in South Africa. The company provides trading in equities, warrants, and exchange-traded products; equity and equity-related futures and options; agricultural grain products and cash-settled derivatives on various commodities, including softs, energy, and various metals; interest rate products; and currency futures and options. It also provides clearing and settlement services; primary market, secondary market, post-trade, and technology services; and information services, including market data, as well as sells live, statistical, historical, and end-of-day data. The company was founded in 1887 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Absa Bank Limited provides various banking products and services primarily in South Africa and Namibia. The company accepts cheque, youth, transactional, and business accounts. Its loan products include personal, express, instant, home, car, study, structured, short and medium term, and trade and working capital loans; vehicle and asset, property, and debt finance; and overdraft and revolving credit facilities. The company also offers credit and debit cards; savings and investment products; home, car, household, life and funeral, travel, will, trust, estate, personal asset risk, and business insurance products; and youth and student, Islamic and international banking, investment management, retirement planning, trust and fiduciary, foreign exchange, and payment services. In addition, it provides corporate banking solutions; corporate finance, equity capital markets, mergers and acquisitions, real estate finance, and ratings advisory services; and capital market products, such as commodities, exchange traded products, retail structures solutions, risk solutions, and equities. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Absa Bank Limited is a subsidiary of Barclays Africa Group Limited.

addressline2: Corner Willie van Schoor Avenue and Old Oak Road
spbusinessdescription: Afrimat Limited, an open pit mining company, engages in the mining, processing, and supply of various aggregates and industrial minerals to the industrial minerals, building, construction, road building, railroad, and mining sectors. The company operates through Mining & Aggregates/Minerals, and Concrete Based Products segments. The Mining & Aggregates/Minerals segment offers aggregates, such as stone and sand; metallurgical dolomite and quartzite; agricultural lime; clinker; and limestone and silica sand, as well as mobile crushing and screening, drilling, and blasting services. The Concrete Based Products segment provides building blocks and bricks, and pavers, as well as ready mix concrete and mortar. It operates in the Western Cape, Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, Free State, Northern Cape, Gauteng, Limpopo, and Mpumalanga, as well as in Mozambique. The company was founded in 1963 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa.

Kumba Iron Ore Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration, extraction, beneficiation, marketing, sale, and shipping of iron ore primarily in South Africa. The company produces iron ore at Sishen and Kolomela mines in the Northern Cape province. It also operates a port in Saldanha Bay, Western Cape. The company supplies its iron ore to the steel industry; and exports to China, Japan, and Korea, as well as various countries in Europe and the Middle East. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa. Kumba Iron Ore Limited is a subsidiary of Anglo South Africa Capital (Proprietary) Limited.

Workforce Holdings Limited provides solutions for the supply, management, and administration of the human resources requirements of various industrial sectors in South Africa and internationally. The company operates in five segments: Staffing and Recruitment, Training and Consulting, Employee Health Management, Financial and Lifestyle Products, and Process Outsourcing segments. The Staffing and Recruitment segment provides staff and labor outsourcing solutions, and recruitment and specialist staffing services, including permanent and temporary placements, ad-response handling, executive search, and skills importing and exporting solutions. The Training and Consulting segment offers industry and job-specific skills assessments and training interventions to business and their employees in various industrial sectors. The Employee Health Management segment provides a range of occupational and primary health management services, and assistance and wellness services. The Financial and Lifestyle Products segment offers a range of lifestyle products and support services to employees and their families. The Process Outsourcing segment provides productive and functional business process outsourcing solutions, including the statutory and legal elements associated therewith.
