Workforce Holdings Limited was founded in 1972 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Accentuate Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the manufacture, distribution, and installation of flooring solutions primarily in South Africa. It also manufactures and supplies chemical cleaning and infrastructural maintenance solutions. It offers floor covering, accessories, self-levelling screeds, vinyl and wood maintenance, engineered and laminated wood floors, textile flooring, and transport flooring products. The company also provides customized chemical and adhesive solutions, including cleaning chemicals and equipment primarily for use in food industry, commercial property, industrial and mining, specialized and vehicle care, floor care, water purification, metal treatment, and cleaning equipment and parts washing. In addition, it offers water and waste water treatment chemicals and equipment comprising water treatment chemicals, ion exchange resins, RO chemicals, flocculants, membranes, waste water treatment plants, sewage treatment plants, design and consulting, turnkey solutions, and water installations. The company was formerly known as SAFIC Holdings Limited and changed its name to Accentuate Limited in May 2008. Accentuate Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Steeledale, South Africa.

CSG Holdings Limited provides outsourced personnel, industrial and mining support, contract catering and food, and cleaning services in South Africa, Mozambique, and Malawi. The company operates in three segments: Staffing Solutions, Facilities Management, and Industrial and Mining Support Services. The Staffing Solutions segment offers temporary outsourced personnel, permanent placements, timekeeping, payroll, human resource, and industrial relations services, as well as contract workers, health and safety audits, employment equity, workforce restructuring, union related matters, and litigation management and support services. The Facilities Management segment manages staff canteens, as well as supplies meals to students, patients in hospitals, corporate head offices, mines, and construction sites. This segment also provides contract catering, events management, laundry, construction camp management, security, pest control and hygiene, and cleaning services. The Industrial and Mining Support Services segment offers plant cleaning, factory cleaning, industrial site and office cleaning, equipment hire, mining construction, and engineering services, as well as confined space safety surveillance - access control, procurement, conveyor system design and manufacturing, shutdown maintenance and management, spillage management, open cast mining, and turnkey projects services. It serves chemical and petro-chemical plants, mines, retail outlets, hospitals, schools, and various other clients, as well as industrial, manufacturing, and transport businesses. The company was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Pretoria, South Africa.

Zeder Investments Ltd. is a private equity arm of PSG Group Ltd. specializing in middle market investments in PIPEs transactions. The firm seeks to invest in unlisted securities of agricultural, food, beverages, grain, and related industries with a focus on agribusiness industry. It seeks to make investments in South Africa and neighboring countries. It invests between ZAR20 million ($2.74 million) and ZAR500 million($49.48 million) in companies with an enterprise values between ZAR50 million (4.95 million) and ZAR10000 million ($989.55 million), revenues between ZAR500 million($49.48 million) and ZAR30000 million ($2968.65 million), and EBITDA between ZAR10 million ($0.99 million) and ZAR2000 million ($197.91 million). The firm sources its capital through equity capital raised through the issuing of share to public shareholders. It invests through its personal capital. Zeder Investments Ltd. was founded in 2006 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Nutritional Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates in the staple food manufacturing, water purification, and renewable energy sectors in the Republic of South Africa. Its Foods division engages in the manufacture and sale of staple dry food products primarily for the mass feeding market, as well as in contract manufacturing business. This division also offers catering products for the industrial catering market. The company's Healthcare Solutions division markets and distributes a range of chlorine free water purification products under license for point of use and industrial customers. This division's products include OneDrop, a point of use water purification drop; and BacSan, an industrial application for municipalities and other bulk water suppliers. Its Services division provides administration and management services. The company also markets and distributes a range of invertors, batteries, and accessories for solar farming, as well as for other industrial security customers; and distributes pharmaceutical, natural, and complementary medicines. Nutritional Holdings Limited is based in Cornubia, the Republic of South Africa.

enX Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides industrial energy equipment, consumables, related components, and support services to various economic sectors in South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. The company operates through Power, Fuel, and Wood business units. It engages in the manufacture, supply, installation, and maintenance of diesel generators and related components, such as industrial engines, marine engines, alternators, switchgears, and components; and distribution of industrial engines, marine engines, and components. The company also rents temporary power in the form of diesel generators and transformers. In addition, it is involved in the distribution and maintenance of professional woodworking equipment, tooling, sharpening, and edging, as well as offers maintenance and after sales services. Further, the company produces, markets, and distributes oil lubricants. It serves clients that range from heavy industrial, mining, and construction groups to wholesalers, retailers, technology and telecommunications companies, banks, and manufacturers. The company was formerly known as Austro Group Limited and changed its name to enX Group Limited in January 2015. enX Group Limited is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

RARE Holdings Limited provides integrated fluid conveyance products and services to the energy, water, and chemical industries in South Africa, Zambia, Ghana, Botswana, Angola, Mali, Guinea, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It operates through four operating divisions: RARE Trading, RARE Pipeline Services, RARE Water Treatment Technology, and RARE Plastics. The RARE Trading division sells various products, such as steel and plastic pipes, fittings, couplings, and valves to the contractors or end users. It also offers cut-to-length, hot stamping, and colour-coding services to the market. The RARE Pipeline Services division provides pipeline installations and pipelining solutions to the mining and industrial sectors. It also supplies and installs various pipe systems, including steel, HDPE lined spool sections for slurry applications, PVC/PVDF, HDPE pipe installations, and cured in place pipe installations for pipeline rehabilitation, as well as double containment HDPE piping for cyanide applications in gold mining. The RARE Water Treatment Technology division provides services ranging from site investigation to design, manufacture, installation, and after-sales on-site support and service maintenance electrochemical treatment plants. These services include site investigation, feed water characterization, and process design; remote monitoring and control; site service maintenance contracts; and electrode management. The RARE Plastics division manufactures and distributes HDPE pipes and fittings. RARE Holdings Limited was founded in 1975 and is headquartered in Midvaal, South Africa. RARE Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Doculate Investments Proprietary Limited.

South Ocean Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily manufactures and sells low voltage electrical cables. The company offers electrical cables focusing on the wholesale sector; and light fittings, lamps/light bulbs, and electrical products, as well as electrical accessories, such as plugs, extension cords, and heaters principally to the construction, infrastructure development and housing, residential, industrial, and commercial markets. It also imports and distributes light fitting products, lamps, electrical accessories, and audio visual hardware and accessories. In addition, the company offers light fittings assembly services; and invests in properties. It sells its products to wholesalers and distributors who supply primarily to the building, construction, mining, and retail industries. South Ocean Holdings Limited was founded in 1989 and is based in Alrode, South Africa.

TeleMasters Holdings Limited engages in the provision of voice, data, and cloud based corporate communication services in South Africa. It offers fixed-line, fixed cellular, fixed data, and virtual PBX services. The company is headquartered in Irene, South Africa. TeleMasters Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Maison D'Obsession Trust.

Rolfes Holdings Limited manufactures and distributes chemical products to various industries in South Africa, the United States, Europe, Asia, and rest of Africa. It operates through Industrial, Water, Agricultural, Food, and Other segments. The Industrial segment manufactures and distributes alkyd resins, organic and inorganic pigments, additives, in-plant and point-of-sale dispersions, leather chemicals products and solutions, food fragrances, food flavourings, solvents, lacquer thinners, surfactants, cleaning solvents, creosotes, waxes, and other industrial chemicals. The Water segment is involved in quarrying and processing of beneficiated silica for the metallurgical, filtration, and construction industries; and provides specialized water purification solutions and products to industrial, agricultural, mining, home and personal care markets. The Agricultural segment manufactures and distributes herbicides, insecticides, fungicides, adjuvants, foliar feeds, enriched compost pellets, and soluble fertilizers used promoting general plant, root, foliage, and soil health. The Food segment imports and distributes chemicals used in the food, beverage, bakery, dairy, pharmaceutical, and cosmetics industries. The Other segment engages in the rental of property, plant, and equipment. The company also provides analytical data. The company was formerly known as Rolfes Technology Holdings Limited and changed its name to Rolfes Holdings Limited in November 2011. Rolfes Holdings Limited was founded in 1925 and is based in Illovo, the Republic of South Africa.

Ansys Limited develops, produces, distributes, and integrates technology-driven engineering solutions for the rail, mining and industrial, telecommunications, and defense and information security sectors in South Africa. The company offers information security, embedded solutions, helmet tracking camera sensors, weapon integration and control systems, mission computers and displays, and test equipment; and system design and integration, bespoke electronic hardware and software development, and contract manufacturing services. It also provides mobile rope testing units, gas detection instruments, collision awareness systems, and equipment and management software. In addition, the company offers trackside systems, such as vehicle identification, hot bearing detection, load profile monitoring, wheel profile monitoring, and integrated train condition; and monitoring systems, including asset tracking, health monitoring, RF ID tags, smart passes, and vandal proof solar power solutions. Further, it provides onboard systems comprising integrated and auxiliary display, train communication, and train definition units; and asset tracking systems. Additionally, the company is involved in the distribution of fiber and data cabling infrastructure, optical wireless broadband and RF products, and network and equipment monitoring solutions; designs, implements, and operates wireless network; designs and implements data centers; and structured cabling and fiber reticulation activities. Ansys Limited was founded in 1987 and is based in Centurion, South Africa.

Interwaste Holdings Limited operates as a waste management company in South Africa, Mozambique, and Swaziland. The company operates through three divisions: Waste Management, Compost Manufacturing, and Landfill Management. It is involved in the collection, transportation, and disposal of waste; management of the environmental consequences of the waste; landfill management and ownership; development and implementation of alternatives to landfill disposal; production of organic compost and related products; and metals recovery and commodity trading activities. The company also offers water and sewerage treatment, specialized industrial cleaning, and on-site waste management services; produces refuse derived fuel; and operates anaerobic digestion biogas project. It also exports its commoditized wastes to 5 countries. The company conducts its business activities under the Interwaste, Envirowaste, and Greens brands. Interwaste Holdings Limited was founded in 1989 and is based in Germiston, South Africa.

Finbond Group Limited operates as a financial services institution. The company offers short and medium-term unsecured loans, secured loans, micro credit products, mortgage finance products, savings products, property investment products, debit cards, insurance products, and transactional banking services. It also provides cellular phone and Internet banking services. The company operates through 379 branches in South Africa and 171 branches in North America. Finbond Group Limited was incorporated in 2001 and is based in Pretoria, the Republic of South Africa.

Hulamin Limited manufactures and markets rolled and extruded aluminum products in South Africa and internationally. It operates in two segments, Hulamin Rolled Products and Hulamin Extrusions. The Hulamin Rolled Products segment offers a range of sheet, coil, and plate products for use in the packaging, automotive and transportation, engineering, and building and construction markets. This segment also produces rigid aluminum foil containers for the catering industry and for household use. The Hulamin Extrusions segment supplies aluminum extrusions to engineering and architectural markets. The company was formerly known as Hulett Aluminium (Pty) Limited and changed its name to Hulamin Limited in 2007. Hulamin Limited was founded in 1935 and is headquartered in Pietermaritzburg, South Africa.

Mondi Limited manufactures and sells packaging and paper products primarily in central Europe, Russia, North America, and the Republic of South Africa. The company operates through Packaging Paper, Fibre Packaging, Consumer Packaging, Uncoated Fine Paper, and South Africa Division segments. Its products include flexible packaging, bags and pouches, films, release liners, personal care components, corrugated packaging, industrial bags, barrier coatings, specialty kraft papers, sack kraft papers, containerboards, and office and professional printing papers. The company serves agriculture, automotive, building and construction, chemicals and dangerous goods, food and beverages, graphic and photographic, home and personal care, medical and pharmaceutical, office and professional printing, paper and packaging converting, pet care, retail and e-commerce, and shipping and transportation industries. Mondi Limited was founded in 1967 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa. Mondi Limited is a subsidiary of The Mondi Group plc.

WG Wearne Limited, together with its subsidiaries, supplies concrete products, aggregates, ready-mix concrete, and premix to the construction industry in South Africa. The company also provides mobile crushing and screening services to mines, civil companies, demolition contractors, and construction companies; laboratory services to ready-mix plants and quarries; and crushing equipment renting services. Its ready-mix concrete products comprise self-levelling, self-compacting, colored and no fines, accelerated set, air entrained, fiber reinforced, pumping, extended workability and reduced slump loss, and high density concrete products, as well as screeds and mortars. The company was founded in 1910 and is headquartered in Cresta, South Africa.

addressline2: Corner Zuurfontein Avenue and Oranjerivier Drive
spbusinessdescription: Stefanutti Stocks Holdings Limited provides construction services in South Africa, sub-Saharan Africa, and the Middle East. It operates through Roads, Pipelines and Mining Services; Mechanical and Electrical; Structures; Building; and Other segments. The company constructs commercial, high-rise, and industrial and service buildings; property development facilities; hotels; healthcare facilities; shopping centers; mass housing; township and residential developments; prefabricated or modular constructions; and PPPs. It also constructs industrial construction projects, such as mining infrastructure and facilities, factories, high volume storage facilities processing plants, smelters, furnaces, mills, petrochemical plants, and auto industry facilities; and undertakes marine and harbor construction projects, which include jetties, docks, quay walls, breakwaters, marine piling, caissons, slipways and boat ramps, structural rehabilitation and concrete repair, control buoy gravity bases, shipyards, digger dredging, and pre-cast concrete for marine structures, as well as environmental projects. In addition, the company provides contract mining, materials handling, tailings management, and technical services for the mining industries; undertakes contracts in the petrochemical industry for constructing new installations, as well as extensions or enhancements to existing operational plants; and constructs power stations, cooling towers, and chimneys through mechanical, electrical, instrumentation, and piping works, as well as constructs traditional coal-fired supply including renewable energy generation projects. Further, it constructs roads, freeways, and transport nodes, as well as related structures and bridges; and various dams, irrigation schemes, and effluent and water treatment plants. Stefanutti Stocks Holdings Limited was founded in 1971 and is based in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Brikor Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and supplies building and construction materials in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Bricks, Aggregates, and Coal. It offers face brick aesthetic clay bricks, plaster bricks, maxi bricks, and semi-face clay bricks, as well as donkerhoek aggregates, including stone, gravel, and sand. The company is also involved in the mining and sale of coal products. It serves housing, residential, commercial, industrial, civil engineering, and infrastructure projects. Brikor Limited is based in Nigel, South Africa.

Huge Group Limited, an investment holding company, operates in the telecommunications, media, technology, and software industries in South Africa. It provides voice, messaging, and data connectivity services using wireless GSM-based, fixed-cellular, and last-mile solutions to residential customers, corporates, and small and medium enterprises. The company also develops billing and rating software, and router products; and software for real time, permission based, and targeted advertising to mobile phones and Internet users. Huge Group Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Ellies Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the manufacture, import, and distribution of television (TV) and video equipment-related products, and satellite and associated equipment under the Ellies and Elsat brand names in the Republic of South Africa. It develops, manufactures, and sells antennae; industrial audio systems; and light metal-fabricated products, such as wall brackets, shelving, satellite and terrestrial mounting brackets, and satellite dishes, as well as TV, VCR, LCD, and plasma mounts. The company also offers remote blasters and video senders; and cryovacing and plastic blister packaging products. In addition, it provides power-related products, including medium voltage withdrawable switchgears, medium voltage fixed pattern switchgears, low voltage switchgears, miniature substations, generators, and distribution transformers. Further, the company offers turnkey project services in the areas of infrastructure development, including in-house project finance, export credit finance, and IPP programs; civil and commercial construction, and property development services; electrical and instrumentation works for the mining, energy, food, petrochemical, power, and heavy industrial sectors; engineering and design services for medium- and high-voltage electrical systems; and water infrastructure and renewable energy services. Additionally, it provides telecommunications towers; and off-grid and green site, and off-grid diesel generator-powered site solutions, as well as data center solutions. The company was founded in 1979 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Imbalie Beauty Limited operates as a franchisor, retailer, distributor, and service provider of skincare, nail care, and other beauty products primarily in South Africa. It offers its products under the Placecol, Skinderm, Scinderm, Beaute Pacifique, Bodyography SKIN, BIOEFFECT, Nsi, Bodyography, and Empro brands. The company also operates and franchises a chain of Placecol skin care clinics; Dream Nails Beauty salons; and Perfect 10 nail and body studios. Its distribution network consists of 150 owned and franchised beauty salons, retailers, independent beauty salons, and pharmacies. The company was formerly known as Skinwell Holdings Limited. Imbalie Beauty Limited was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Woodmead, South Africa.

RBA Holdings Limited develops housing properties primarily in South Africa. It operates through two segments, Property Development Activities and Sectional Title Rental Activities. The company's principal product offerings include bonded homes sold to prospective new homeowners; and the development and delivery of rental units to institutional market participants and property investors that hold residential rental portfolios. It engages in the provision of land procurement, town planning and urban design, architectural and civil engineering expertise, and legal administration services for the property development and construction process, as well as construction, and marketing and sales services. The company was founded in 1997 and is based in Braamfontein, South Africa.

BSi Steel Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the processing, warehouse, distribution, and sale of steel and allied products in South Africa and the rest of Africa. It operates in four segments: Stockists, Bulk Sales, Exporting, and Other. The company offers flat products, including hot and cold rolled, galvanized, color-coated, aluzinc, and electro-plated products; and plates, such as structural grade, quenched and tempered, and boiler plates. It also provides long products comprising beams and columns, channels, angles, and reinforcing bars; and round, square, and flat bars, as well as light sections. In addition, the company offers corrugated, IBR, and wide-span roofing products; round, square, and rectangular tubing products; lipped channels; slit strips and precision blanks; cut to length sheets and plates; and profile cut plates and sheets. Further, it engages in the rental of property. BSi Steel Limited was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Pietermaritzburg, South Africa.
MiX Telematics Limited provides fleet and mobile asset management solutions through software-as-a-service delivery model worldwide.

addressline2: Corner of Grayston Drive & Benmore Drive
spbusinessdescription: Blue Label Telecoms Limited engages in the virtual distribution of electronic tokens of value and transactional activities in South Africa, India, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. It operates through South African Distribution, International Distribution, Mobile, and Solutions segments. The South African Distribution segment distributes prepaid products and transactional services, including starter packs, physical airtime vouchers, virtual vouchers, bulk print solutions, prepaid electricity and water vouchers, international calling cards, bill payment, ticketing, lotto, financial services, prepaid electricity vending, arrears collection, meter audits, data cleansing, debt collection, hybrid discounted airtime contract, and network postpaid contract services, as well as vending machine, kiosk touch screen, POS terminal, gateway for integrated POS, and mobi merchant solutions to the South African wholesale and retail markets. The International Distribution segment offers physical prepaid products and starter packs; label investments; PINless recharge, direct top-up, and payment services; and service aggregation and distribution, online payment processing, and money transfer services through mobile, POS, and Web to telecom/DTH operators, and various service providers and banks. The Mobile segment provides mobile transactional ecosystem and services provisioning platform delivering mobile-centric products and services through mobile channel, including location-based and WASP services, and music and digital content. The Solutions segment markets cellular and financial products and services through outbound telemarketing and other channels; and data and analytics services, as well as provides inbound customer care and technical support services. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

KayDav Group Limited engages in distributing wood-based panels through its outlets in the Western Cape, Southern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, and Gauteng, South Africa. The company operates in Board Distribution and Adaptation, and Packaging segments. It offers wood-based panels under the Kayreed Board and Timber, and Davidson's Discount Boards brands for the furniture, shop-fitting, and kitchen manufacturing and installation industries, as well as to other wood-based panel distributors. The company also provides packaging consumables and machinery through its outlets in Western Cape and Gauteng for various customers, including manufacturers, agriculture, home industries, and small businesses under the Packit Packaging Solutions trade name. KayDav Group Limited is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Calgro M3 Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the mixed-use/integrated residential properties development activities in South Africa. It operates through three segments: Property Development, Professional Services, and Memorial Parks. The company develops integrated, affordable, mid-high income housing properties; and memorial parks, as well as rents residential properties. It also offers land acquisition, town planning, architecture, civil infrastructure project management, installation, and home marketing and construction services. The company serves the government, financial institutions, and the general public. Calgro M3 Holdings Limited was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

ARB Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading and distribution of electrical, lighting, and related products. It operates through three segments: Electrical, Lighting, and Corporate. The company provides power and instrumentation cables, overhead line hardware and conductors, insulators, transformers, general electrical contracting materials, and general low-voltage products to large and heavy industry, government and parastatal, construction, mining, electrical contractor, and domestic/do-it-yourself (DIY) markets. It also imports and distributes incandescent, energy saving, LED, and fluorescent lamps; light fittings; commercial and project lighting products; and a range of electrical accessories, as well as ancillary products, including fans and lighting components to retail chains, independent DIY chains, hardware stores, specialized lighting shops, and electrical wholesalers. In addition, the company sells computer hardware; and provides specialist IT hardware, and software and support services, as well as holds and rents a portfolio of 15 properties. ARB Holdings Limited was founded in 1980 and is based in Durban, South Africa.

Mazor Group Limited designs, supplies, and installs structural steelwork and aluminum facades for the industrial, construction, and infrastructure markets in the Republic of South Africa. It operates through three divisions: Steel, Aluminium, and Glass. The Steel division designs, supplies, and erects structural steel frames for industrial and retail buildings, including shopping centers, warehouses, buildings, bridges, and architectural work. The Aluminium division designs, manufactures, and installs aluminum structures, such as doors, windows, shop fronts, facades, balustrades, and custom solutions for blue-chip construction groups. This division also supplies aluminum fenestration systems. The Glass division manufactures and distributes laminated, toughened safety, and processed glasses. Mazor Group Limited was founded in 1981 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited, an infrastructure-focused company, operates in the power, mining, logistics, and waste management sectors in Africa and the Middle East. The company operates through Power, Building Materials, Oil and Gas, and Rail divisions. It supplies high voltage infrastructure for governments, utilities, municipalities, and mining and finance houses, as well as the industrial sector; and provides power maintenance services in the renewable energy sector. The company also mines, manufactures, and supplies face, semi-faced, and plaster clay bricks, as well as various concrete roof tiles to the building sector, including developers, contractors, and wholesalers; and aggregates, such as sand, gravel, and crushed stone to commercial and civil building contractors. In addition, it collects, recycles, and disposes oil-based waste created during the drilling process for the industrial and natural resources exploration sectors. Further, Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited provides rail infrastructure service, including railway and power solutions, and maintenance. The company was formerly known as Buildworks Group Limited and changed its name to Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited in September 2010. Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited is based in Sandhurst, South Africa.

Vunani Limited provides financial products and services primarily in South Africa. The company operates through Fund Management, Asset Administration, Advisory Services, Institutional Securities Broking, Private Equity, and Private Wealth and Investments segments. It offers single asset class products, such as managed equity, bonds, inflation-linked bonds and property; multi-asset class products comprising absolute return and alternative return; and fundamental and market cap indexation beta products. The company also offers a trading platform for high net worth individuals to trade their portfolios, derivatives, and hedging instruments; manages portfolios on behalf of private clients; a range of products, including geared derivatives and money market accounts; and absolute, balanced, and directional funds. In addition, it provides investment banking services, such as corporate advisory services to public sector entities, corporations, entrepreneurs, municipalities, financial sponsors, and boards of directors; and capital-raising services. Further, the company offers stockbroking services to institutional and retail clients. The company was incorporated in 1997 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Vunani Limited is a subsidiary of Vunani Group (Pty) Ltd.

Insimbi Refractory and Alloy Supplies Limited provides ferrous and non-ferrous alloys, and refractory materials for the steel, aluminum, cement, and foundry industries in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Foundry, Refractory, Steel, and Plastics segments. The Foundry segment supplies various alloys and ancillary raw materials, such as foundry sand and ceramic ducting to ferrous and non-ferrous foundries, including heavy-duty foundries, automotive foundries, electroplating specialists, etc. The Refractory segment supplies specialized ceramic refractory linings to cement, paper and pulp, steel, and platinum industries. The Steel segment supplies various alloys that include non-ferrous alloys to the steel and stainless steel industry. The Plastics segment engages in the blowmoulding of plastic containers for the chemical, agricultural, and food industries. The company was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Germiston, South Africa.

Keaton Energy Holdings Limited, a coal mining company, engages in the mining, exploration, extraction, and processing of coal. It explores for thermal and metallurgical coal, and anthracite. The company's flagship project is the Vanggatfontein colliery that is located to the south-east of Delmas, Mpumalanga. It also operates other projects in KwaZulu-Natal in South Africa. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

Pioneer Food Group Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells food, beverage, and related products for human and animal consumption in South Africa. It operates through Essential Foods, Groceries, International, and Other segments. The company produces breakfast cereals, rusks, cake mixes, baking aids and desserts, dried fruits, nuts, sweet and savory spreads, processed salads, fruit juices, fruit concentrate mixtures, ice tea, bottled water, and dairy fruit blends. It also manufactures and sells wheat, maize, and pasta products; and supplies rice, beans and legumes, and other dried vegetables, as well as engages in bakery operations. The company sells its products primarily under the Weet-Bix, Liqui-Fruit, Ceres, Sasko, Safari, Spekko, and White Star brand names to the wholesale, retail, and trade customers. Pioneer Food Group Ltd also exports its products to approximately 60 countries worldwide. The company was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Tyger Valley, South Africa.

eXtract Group Limited provides contract mining services in South Africa, Botswana, and Namibia. The company offers opencast mining services comprising drilling, blasting, loading, hauling, and rehabilitation services. The company was formerly known as Eqstra Holdings Limited and changed its name to eXtract Group Limited in November 2016. eXtract Group Limited was founded in 1984 and is based in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Clientele Limited provides financial products and services in South Africa. It operates in four segments: Long-Term Insurance, Investment Contracts, Short-Term Insurance, and Loans Business. The company underwrites, markets, and distributes insurance and investment products principally on a direct distribution basis. It offers funeral, hospital, legal, and life insurance products. The company also provides personal loans; and investment solutions, which comprise wealth, guaranteed income, and growth plans, as well as financial advisory services. In addition, it offers short-term insurance products, such as personal and business lines legal insurance policies. The company is headquartered in Morningside, South Africa. Clientele Limited is a subsidiary of Pickent Investments Limited.

Grand Parade Investments Limited is a private equity firm specializing in incubation, PIPE's, industry consolidation, recapitalizations, buyouts, and growth capital investments. It considers investments in middle market, mature, turnaround, and emerging growth stages. The firm typically invests in leisure, tourism, and gaming sectors and also considers investments in property, retail, food, manufacturing, and entertainment. It seeks to invest in Africa with a focus on South Africa  and Western Cape. The firm primarily invests between R$10 million ($0.84 million) and R$1000 million ($84.98 million) in companies with enterprise value greater than R$300 million ($25.50 million). The firm prefers to take a board seat in its portfolio companies. It may enter into joint ventures and other similar alliances, whereby it forms partnerships with such entities, contributing not only capital, but also providing strategic managerial input. The firm seeks to take more than 20 per cent stake, however a smaller stake is also considered where there is the potential to increase such stake in the future. It seeks to make balance sheet investments. Grand Parade Investments Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Alaris Holdings Limited engages in the design, manufacture, and sale of antennas in South Africa and internationally. The company provides broadband antennas, as well as other related radio frequency products to system integrators, frequency spectrum regulators, and players in the homeland security space for use in the communication, frequency spectrum monitoring, test and measurement, electronic warfare, and other specialized markets. It also offers antenna products, serving military and public safety markets; and integrated broadcasting systems for radio and TV broadcasters for use in digital compression platforms for digital terrestrial television, direct to home and Internet protocol television, signal distribution, and multiscreen, as well as over-the-top systems. The company was formerly known as Poynting Holdings Limited and changed its name to Alaris Holdings Limited in May 2015. Alaris Holdings Limited was founded in 1990 and is based in Centurion, South Africa.

Efficient Group Ltd provides various financial services in South Africa. It operates through three segments: Financial Services, Services and Solutions, and Investments. The Financial Services segment offers financial planning, asset finance, investment management, life and business assurance, short-term insurance, stockbroking, and cash management solutions to target markets through a network of financial advisors. The Services and Solutions segment provides portfolio and multi-managed funds solutions for financial planners, individuals, and intuitional clients. The Investments segment offers collective investment scheme administration, fund and private client wealth management, and investment consultation services for retail and institutional investors. The company is headquartered in Pretoria, South Africa.

Vodacom Group Limited, a unified communications provider, offers mobile voice, messaging, data, financial, and converged services to the consumer, business, and enterprise customers in South Africa and internationally.

Sephaku Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiary, Metier Mixed Concrete (Pty) Ltd, operates as a building and construction materials company in South Africa. It manufactures and supplies ready-mixed concrete products for the residential, commercial, and industrial markets. Sephaku Holdings Limited is based in Irene, South Africa.

addressline1: Corner of Hulley and Gewel Avenue
spbusinessdescription: Wescoal Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in mining, processing, supplying, selling, and distributing coal and coal-related products primarily in South Africa. The company operates through two divisions, Mining and Trading. It is involved in the exploration, beneficiation, and mining of coal; and trading of coal and related products, including small nuts, industrial peas, duff, and anthracite. The company's flagship mine is the Elandspruit colliery that contains five mineable coal seams located on the old Witbank road in the Mpumalanga province, as well as holds interests in the Intibane colliery and Khanyisa colliery mines. It also provides logistical requirements for the sourcing, distribution, and delivery of coal products to the general industry with emphasis on road transportation. The company sources and supplies coal to clients in power generation and manufacturing sectors. Wescoal Holdings Limited is based in Isando, South Africa.

Taste Holdings Limited owns and licenses a portfolio of franchised and owned, category specialist and formula driven, quick service restaurant, and retail brands in South Africa. The company's Food division offers coffee, chicken, pizza, and fish products, as well as breakfast and burgers. This division's brand portfolio includes Starbucks Coffee, Domino's Pizza, Scooters Pizza, St Elmo's, Maxi's, The Fish & Chip Co, and Zebro's Chicken. Its Luxury Goods division manufactures and supplies jewelry; and retails watches. This division operates jewelry outlets under the Natal Wholesale Jewellers, Arthur Kaplan, and World's Finest Watches brands. Taste Holdings Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Royal Bafokeng Platinum Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in mining and producing platinum group metals in the Republic of South Africa. It holds a 67% joint venture interest in the Bafokeng Rasimone Platinum Mine, as well as engages in the construction of the Styldrift I Project located in the North West province of South Africa. The company was incorporated in 2008 and is based in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa.

Clover Industries Limited produces and distributes dairy and non-dairy beverage consumer products. It operates through Dairy fluids, Concentrated Products, Ingredients, Non-alcoholic Beverages, and Fermented Products and Desserts segments. The company offers dairy fluid products, such as fresh milk, UHT milk, steri milk, ultra-pasteurized milk, and cream; concentrated dairy products, including cheese, butter, condensed milk, and retail milk powders; bulk milk powders, bulk butter, bulk condensed milk, bulk creamers, calf feed substitutes, whey powders, and buttermilk powders; non-alcoholic beverage products comprising fruit juices, dairy fruit mixes, flavored milk, water, and ice tea; and yoghurt, maas, custard, and other dessert products. It also provides laboratory services for dairy and dairy-related industries; distributes and sells chilled and ambient consumer products of other brands; and manufactures and distributes soya based milk alternatives and a range of functional food products. The company serves customers through its distribution centers in South Africa, as well as exports its products. The company was formerly known as National Co-operative Dairies Limited and changed its name to Clover Industries Limited in 2003. Clover Industries Limited was founded in 1898 and is based in Roodepoort, South Africa.

addressline3: Corner of Fredman Drive and Rivonia Road
spbusinessdescription: Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides a range of financial products and services in South Africa, Australia, New Zealand, and the United Kingdom. It operates through Discovery, MMI, and OUTsurance segments. The Discovery segment offers integrated financial services to the healthcare funding and insurance markets under the Discovery Health, Discovery Life, Discovery Invest, Discovery Vitality, Discovery Insure, Discovery Vitality, VitalityHealth, VitalityLife, and Ping An Health brand names. The MMI segment provides life insurance, employee benefits, investment and savings, healthcare solutions, and short-term insurance services to individual clients, small and medium businesses, large companies, organizations, and public enterprises under the Momentum and Metropolitan brands. The OUTsurance segment offers short and long-term insurance products, as well as personal lines insurance products. The company was formerly known as Rand Merchant Insurance Holdings Limited and changed its name to Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited in January 2016. Rand Merchant Investment Holdings Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Curro Holdings Limited develops, acquires, and manages independent schools in South Africa and Namibia. It operates through Curro, Meridian, and Embury segments. The company operates nursery, primary, and high schools, as well as provides balanced academics, sport, and culture services. It operates Curro schools that accommodate learners from age 3 to grade 12; Meridian and Curro Academy schools, which accommodate learners from age 5 to grade 12; and Curro Castles nursery schools, which accommodate learners from 3 months to 5 years old, as well as Curro Select schools. The company also operates Embury Institute for Teacher Training, a private higher education institution that offers full-time teacher education qualifications, as well as in-service training for practicing teachers. As of December 31, 2016, it operated 54 campuses and 127 schools accommodating 47,589 learners, which include the teachers training college accommodating approximately 950 students. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Durbanville, the Republic of South Africa. Curro Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of PSG Financial Services Ltd.

Mpact Limited manufactures and sells paper and plastic packaging products in South Africa and other African regions. It operates through Paper and Plastics segments. The Paper segment offers recycled-based packaging and industrial paper grades, such as containerboards and carton boards; and a range of printed and unprinted converted corrugated products, including boards for use in the manufacture of corrugated packaging, corrugated boxes, die-cut cases, folded glued cases, trays, and point-of-sale displays. It also sells Baywhite, a white top Kraftliner; and recycles paper through various recovered paper sources comprising pre- and post-consumer material sourced through a range of paper pickup programs. This segment markets its packaging and industrial paper products to corrugated board and box producers, and other containerboard converters; carton boards to folding carton converters and other producers of industrial products, as well as the manufacturers of cards and book covers; and corrugated products to producers of agricultural, fast moving consumer goods (FMCG), and other durable and non-durable goods. The Plastics segment manufactures various plastic packaging products, such as polyethylene terephthalate (PET) preforms, bottles, and jars; closures for carbonated soft drinks, water, and food; and plastic jumbo bins, environmental wheelie bins, and plastic pallets and crates. This segment also provides plastic FMCG containers, including bottles, tubs, jars, and closures; and styrene and PET trays, and clear plastic films, as well as recycled-based PET products. It serves the food, beverage, personal care, home care, pharmaceutical, agricultural, environmental, and retail markets. The company is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Holdsport Limited engages in the retail of sports and outdoor related footwear, apparel, and equipment in South Africa. It operates through Sportsmans Warehouse, Outdoor Warehouse, and Wholesale segments. The company is also involved in the design, manufacture, import, and distribution of technical and sports apparel and accessories to the sporting and outdoor industry under the First Ascent, Capestorm, Second Skins, and African Nature brands. It operates through a network of 39 Sportsmans Warehouse stores and 24 Outdoor Warehouse stores. Holdsport Limited was founded in 1986 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Arrowhead Properties Limited, a property loan stock company, is engaged in holding, leasing, and managing a portfolio of properties in South Africa. Its property portfolio includes retail, commercial, residential, and industrial properties. The company's tenants comprise large listed and national tenants, medium and large professional firms, government, and franchisees. Arrowhead Properties Limited was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Texton Property Fund Limited is a real estate investment trust externally managed by Texton Property Investments Proprietary Limited. It invests in the real estate markets of South Africa. The firm engages in management, development, and acquisition of office and retail properties. It was formerly known as Vunani Property Investment Fund Limited. Texton Property Fund Limited was formed in 2006 and is based in South Africa.

Transaction Capital Limited provides non-deposit taking financial services in South Africa. It operates through two divisions, SA Taxi and Transaction Capital Risk Services. The SA Taxi division provides finance, insurance, and other related products primarily for small-to-medium enterprise (SMEs) in the fixed route minibus taxi industry. The Transaction Capital Risk Services division offers customer management and capital solutions, including the collection of accounts receivable across credit lifecycle; business support and working capital finance; and personal credit information, as well as tailor-made services. This division works with large consumer credit providers across various industries, such as banking, credit retail, telecommunications, insurance, specialist lending, the public sector, and SMEs. Transaction Capital Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.
Dipula Income Fund Limited specializes in making real estate investments.

Capevin Holdings Limited operates as an investment holding company in South Africa. The company, through its 26.77% interest in Distell Group Limited, produces and markets spirits, wines, ciders, and ready-to-drinks. Capevin Holdings Limited is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Gooderson Leisure Corporation Limited, an investment holding company, owns and manages various leisure destinations in South Africa. It operates through Hotels and Lodges, and Timeshare divisions. The company manages and provides accommodation, conference and wedding facilities, food and beverage, and restaurant services to leisure, international, and conference tourists in KwaZulu Natal, Limpopo, Gauteng, and Mpumalanga provinces. Its leisure portfolio comprises the Tropicana Hotel, and the Beach Hotel in Durban; the Drakensberg Gardens Golf & Spa Resort in southern Drakensberg; and the Bushlands Game Lodge, and the DumaZulu Lodge & Traditional Village in Hluhluwe. The company's leisure portfolio also includes the Natal Spa Hot Springs & Leisure resort in Paulpietersburg; the Monks Cowl Golf Resort in Central Drakensberg; Kloppenheim Country Estate hotel in Dullstroom; Fabz Garden Hotel & Conference Centre in Johannesburg; and the SanRock Resort & Conference Centre in Modimolle. In addition, it manages timeshare resorts that include Fairways, Riverbend Chalets, and Mountainview Cottages at Drakensberg Gardens; Silversands I, II, III Lifestyle Resort in Durban; and Mtunzini Forest Lodge Lifestyle Resort at Mtunzini. The company was founded in 1957 and is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

Niveus Investments Limited, an investment holding company, operates in the gaming and entertainment, and alcoholic beverage sectors in South Africa and internationally. The company offers limited payout machine gaming services; and operates licensed bingo centers. It is also involved in purchasing grapes and wine; and distilling, marketing, and selling wine, spirits, and brandy products under the Roodeberg, KWV Wines, Laborie, Golden Kaan, and Cathedral Cellar brand names, as well as KWV 3, 5, 10, 15, and 20 Year Old brandies. The company was formerly known as HCI Growth Limited and changed its name to Niveus Investments Limited in November 2012. The company is based in Paarl, South Africa. Niveus Investments Limited is a subsidiary of Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited.

Master Drilling Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides specialized drilling services to blue chip major and mid-tier companies in the mining, civil engineering, construction, and hydro-electric power sectors. The company offers surface and underground raise boring, underground and surface exploration drilling, and blind hole boring services; and boxhole boring and drilling services. It also provides exploration drilling services, such as auger, percussion rotary air blast, air-core, reverse-circulation, diamond-core, direct-push, hydraulic rotary, sonic vibratory, underground, blasthole, and grade control drilling services, as well as horisontal raise boring and value-added services. As of March 22, 2017, the company operated a fleet of 105 raise bore and 33 slim drilling rigs in Africa, Latin America, South Africa, and internationally. Master Drilling Group Limited was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Fochville, South Africa.

Torre Industries Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the capital equipment, parts and components, and analytical services businesses in the Republic of South Africa. The Capital Equipment segment sells and rents heavy lifting and earth moving equipment to the mining, agriculture, and construction industries. The Parts and Components segment supplies aftermarket spare parts to the automotive, construction, mining, and agriculture industries. The Analytical Services segment provides scientific analysis and laboratorial services to various customers and industries. The company was formerly known as Torre Industrial Holdings Limited and changed its name to Torre Industries Limited in June 2014. Torre Industries Limited was founded in 2012 and is based in Modderfontein, South Africa.
Atterbury Investment Holdings Limited is a real estate investment firm based in Pretoria, South Africa.

Ascendis Health Limited manufactures and distributes health and care products to the plant, and animal and human health markets in South Africa and internationally. It operates through four segments: Consumer Brands, Pharma-Med, Phyto-Vet, and International. The company offers over the counter (OTC) medicines and consumer brands products, including vitamins and minerals, homeopathic and herbal products, dermaceuticals, functional foods, functional super foods, sports nutrition products, health beverages, weight management products, and therapeutic cosmetics. It also sells prescription and selected OTC pharmaceuticals, as well as medical devices; and supplies health and care products to the plant and animal markets covering approximately 4,500 retail stores. The company sells its products primarily under the Solal, Evox, SSN, Bolus, Sportron, and Swissgarde brands. Ascendis Health Limited was incorporated in 2008 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Safari Investments RSA Limited operates as a property investment company in South Africa. It has 4 regional shopping centres that has net lettable area of approximately 97 529 square meters in Gauteng. The company qualifies as a real estate investment trust for federal income tax purposes. It generally would not be subject to federal corporate income taxes if it distributes at least 90% of its taxable income to its stockholders. The company was incorporated in 2000 and is based in Pretoria, South Africa.

Advanced Health Limited, an investment holding company, provides short-procedure surgical facilities and services in day hospitals in Australia and South Africa. It provides surgical procedure services in the areas of dental and maxillo facial, ophthalmology, general surgery, gynaecology, plastic surgery, orthopaedic, and urology, as well as ear, nose, and throat. The company is based in Pretoria, South Africa.

PSG Konsult Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides various financial services and products in South Africa and Namibia. It operates through three segments: PSG Wealth, PSG Asset Management, and PSG Insure. The PSG Wealth segment offers portfolio management, stockbroking, local and offshore investments, estate planning, financial planning, local and offshore fiduciary, employee benefits, multi-managed investment solutions, securities, and retirement products to individuals, families, and businesses. The PSG Asset Management segment provides various investment products, including local and international unit trust funds; and investment management services to long-term retail and institutional investors. The PSG Insure segment offers personal short-term insurance products, including home, car, and household insurance; and commercial short-term insurance products, such as business and agri-insurance. The company was incorporated in 1993 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa. PSG Konsult Limited is a subsidiary of PSG Financial Services Limited.

Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited provides integrated retirement, investment, life, and insurance solutions for individuals and businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company's solutions for individuals cover money management, budgeting for financial well-being, savings, investments, retirement, medical scheme plan and health insurance, insurance to protect wealth and assets, life and risk cover, and wills and estate planning. Its solutions for businesses cover consulting and actuarial services; retirement fund services; healthcare consulting, health management solutions, and technical advisory services; group and business insurance services that cover assets, earnings, and the legal liabilities of business against loss or damage; services that cover emerging markets in Arica; and trust and beneficiary services that cover the management of benefits for beneficiaries of deceased retirement fund and group life scheme members. The company was formerly known as Alexander Forbes Equity Holdings Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited in June 2014. Alexander Forbes Group Holdings Limited is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

Anchor Group Limited, a financial services holding company, provides asset management products and services to private and offshore clients. It also offers financial education and research, as well as provides trading and portfolio management services. The company was formerly known as Andotorque Investments Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Anchor Group Limited in July 2014. Anchor Group Limited was founded in 2009 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Quantum Foods Holdings Limited engages in feeds and poultry business primarily in South African markets. It operates through Eggs, Farming, and Animal Feeds segments. The company produces and distributes eggs; and sells layer parent stock, day-old pullets, and point-of-lay hens in South Africa, Namibia, Botswana, Swaziland, and Mozambique under the Bergvlei Chicks brand. It also supplies livestock to abattoirs and day-old chickens from hatcheries; and produces and sells various feeds, including broiler, layer, dairy, sheep, cattle, ostrich, and pig feeds under the Nova Feeds name. The company was incorporated in 2013 and is based in Wellington, South Africa.

Rhodes Food Group Holdings Limited manufactures and markets convenience food products in South Africa and Swaziland. It operates through Regional and International segments. The company offers canned fruits, jams, tomato products, and canned meat, as well as canned and bottled salads and vegetables; juice products; fruit pulps, purees, and concentrates; fresh and frozen ready meals, as well as pies and pastries; and dairy products, such as milk, cream, and cheese. It also engages in the rental of investment properties. The company provides its products under the Rhodes, Bull Brand, Hazeldene, Spekenam, Apex, Magpie, Saint Pie, Wilde, Zing, Crystal Falls, Trout Hall, and Squish brands. Rhodes Food Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1893 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Montauk Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, develops, owns, and operates renewable energy projects utilizing landfill methane in the United States. It sells natural gas and electricity. The company was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited engages in the mining and exploration of mineral resources in South Africa. The company primarily mines and explores for uranium and gold deposits, as well as mines and supplies thermal coal. It owns Shiva Uranium mine that is located near Klerksdorp in the North-West province; and Brakfontein project, which is located near Delmas in the Mpumalanga province, South Africa. The company was formerly known as Clidet 1018 Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited in February 2010. Oakbay Resources and Energy Limited was incorporated in 2009 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

The Pivotal Fund Limited is a real estate investment firm. It was founded in 2005 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. As per the transaction announced on August 30, 2016, The Pivotal Fund Limited operates as a subsidiary of Redefine Properties Limited.

addressline3: Corner Rooihuiskraal and Hendrik Verwoerd Drives
spbusinessdescription: Acsion Limited operates as a property developer and property holding company in South Africa. The company's developed investment properties consist of six retail properties and one light industrial/commercial property with a total gross lettable area of 204,454 square meters located in Gauteng, Mpumalanga, and Limpopo. It also holds development assets comprising residential accommodation, retail, petrol station, and convenience shopping center properties; a housing development held for sale in Walkraal, Limpopo; and residential units and residential land opportunities held for sale in Hyde Park, Gauteng. The company was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Centurion, South Africa.

Cartrack Holdings Limited provides fleet management, stolen vehicle recovery, and insurance telematics services in South Africa. The company offers Bike Recovery, a wireless, self-powered, and waterproof tracking device for stolen motorbike recovery; Bike Track, a real-time GPS/GSM telematics solution for commercial motorbikes; Bike Track with the stolen vehicle recovery services; and Asset Track, a wireless and self-powered GPS/GSM tracking unit, which helps you track and monitor the movement of movable asset. It also provides Drive vision, an on-board dual camera system that comprises a primary camera that records video footage with a 120-degree exterior view of the road ahead, and plus secondary driver camera that provides a 160-degree view of the inside of the vehicle cab; Communicator, a software application for mobile tablets and phones that combines communication, navigation, tracking and task management technologies into one solution. In addition, the company offers Mi-Fleet, an administrative and vehicle cost accounting software. It also operates in Europe, South East Asia, the United States, and New Zealand. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Cartrack Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Onecell Holdings Proprietary Limited.

Novus Holdings Limited provides commercial printing services in South Africa. It operates through two segments, Printing and Other. The Printing segment engages in the printing of inserts, newspapers, security products, magazines, commercial works, annual reports, examination materials, ballots, books, and directories. The Other segment is involved in the printing of flexible labels for wine, beer, spirit, cosmetics, petrochemical, food, and beverage markets; and manufacture of tissues, including one and two-ply toilet rolls, kitchen towels and serviettes, and jumbo waddings. The company was founded in 1905 and is headquartered in Milnerton, South Africa. Novus Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Media24 Proprietary Limited.

Nvest Financial Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides financial products and services in South Africa. It offers financial advice and intermediary services in personal and commercial lines in the short term insurance industry; and portfolio management services. The company also engages in acquiring, holding, and managing a portfolio of properties, and for the purpose of the issue of commercial paper; and in the preparation of wills, managed accounts, and the administration of deceased estates and testamentary trusts. Nvest Financial Holdings Limited was founded in 1985 and is based in East London, South Africa.

Sygnia Limited provides investment management and administration services to institutional and retail clients primarily in South Africa. The company offers a range of investment products, including multi-manager funds, index tracking funds, and funds of South African hedge funds; and stockbroking, as well as a range of savings products. It also provides investment administration services comprising multi-tier unitization, consolidated administration reporting, consolidated financial accounting information, cash flow management with optimized rebalancing, monitoring of compliance with mandates and with legislation, monitoring of management and performance fees charged by asset managers, regulatory reporting, performance and risk analysis reporting, asset liability modelling reviews, and transition management services. The company is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Sygnia Limited is a subsidiary of Zatoka Trust.

Trellicor (pty) Ltd. designs, manufactures, and sells physical home security and commercial property security products. The company offers security gates and burglar guards, including powder coated galvanized steel security barriers, non-retractable galvanized steel security barriers, and rollerstyle aluminum shutters; security systems for doors and windows; and burglar guards for windows. Its products are used to protect domestic homes and commercial buildings, such as banks, prisons, retail outlets, airports, schools, and stadiums from break-ins by unwanted intruders. The company sells its products through a franchise network and stores in South Africa and other Internationally. Trellicor (pty) Ltd. was founded in 1976 and is based in Durban North, South Africa.

Stor-Age Property REIT Limited is a real estate investment trust. the firm invests in the real estate markets of South Africa. It is focused on the ownership, acquisition, development and management of prime self storage assets. Stor-Age Property REIT Limited was formed in 2006 and is based in South Africa.

Global Asset Management Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides forklift truck rental and maintenance services in the Republic of South Africa. It also sells forklift trucks; and offers project management, corporate, and other services. In addition, the company provides project and structured finance, asset finance, export credit finance, DTI grants, and loan and/or working capital facility restructuring services, as well as property development services, including designing and implementing funding structures for residential and commercial property developments. Further, it offers debt and mezzanine capital for large infrastructure projects; and engages in renewable energy and energy efficiency equipment installation funding businesses, as well as rubber and plastic recycling activities. The company was founded in 1992 and is based in Roodepoort, the Republic of South Africa. Global Asset Management Limited is a subsidiary of Inshare Proprietary Limited.

Gold Brands Investments Limited operates as a franchising company in South Africa. It franchises various stores under the Chesanyama, 1+1 Pizza, Opa!Pitaland, Chicken Wild Wings, and Blacksteer, as well as Hot Chicks brands. The company was founded in 2012 and is based in Pretoria, South Africa.

Sasol Inzalo Public Limited (RF), through its investment in Sasol Limited, operates as an integrated energy and chemicals company in South Africa and internationally. It manufactures and sells base chemical products, including fertilizers, polymers, and solvents; performance chemicals, such as surfactants, surfactant intermediates, fatty alcohols, linear alkyl benzene, short-chain linear alpha olefins, ethylene, mineral oil-based and synthetic paraffin waxes, cresylic acids, and carbon solutions, as well as high-purity alumina and specialty gases; fuels and oils, such as automotive and industrial lubricants, greases, cleansers and degreases, and automotive and burner fuels; and polyethylene, polypropylene, polyvinyl chloride polymers, as well as explosives. The company also offers low-carbon electricity; operates coal mines that supply feedstock, as well as coal to the international power generation customers; and develops and manages the upstream interests in oil and gas exploration and production in Mozambique, South Africa, Canada, Gabon, and Australia. Its products are used in the production of hot-melt adhesives, car products, microchip coatings, printing inks, household and industrial paints, mobile phone circuit boards, transport fuels, compact discs, medical lasers, sun creams, perfumes, and plastic bottles. The company was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Visual International Holdings Limited engages in the property holding and development business in the Republic of South Africa. It operates in three segments: Property Services, Property Investment, and Property Development. The company primarily develops and sells residential, commercial, and retail projects. It is also involved in letting residential properties; and providing management, administration, and consulting services on development projects. The company was formerly known as Presto Financing Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Visual International Holdings Limited in October 2013. Visual International Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is based in Stellenberg, the Republic of South Africa.

Dis-Chem Pharmacies Limited owns and operates a chain of pharmacy stores, family clinics, and medication centers. The company operates through Retail and Wholesale segments. It offers dispensary products, including diagnostics, first aid, mobility and incontinence, and OTC remedies; beauty products, including beauty accessories, color cosmetics, face care, fragrance, and skin care; toiletries products, including bath care, bathroom, body care, deodorants, foot care, hair care, intimate care, oral care, and shaving products; vitamins and nutraceuticals, and homeopathic and herbal products; sports supplements, and sports equipment and aids; and foods and specialized diet. The company also provides electrical products, including heating and cooling, household, and lifestyle; household products, including cleaners and fresheners, homeware, insecticides, kitchen, kitchen tools, purifiers, storage, and veterinary; and seasonal cards and gifts. It also sells products online, as well as operates hair and beauty salons. Dis-Chem Pharmacies Limited has approximately 101 stores in South Africa; and two partner stores in Namibia. The company was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Premier Food and Fishing Limited offers technical maintenance of shipping vessels. The company was formerly known as Sekunjalo Industrial Holdings Proprietary Limited. Premier Food and Fishing Limited was founded in 1952 and is based in South Africa.

Sea Harvest Group Limited engages in the fishing and food business servicing retail and foodservice customers. Its activities include the fishing of Cape Hake and Shark Bay prawns, processing of the catch into frozen and chilled seafood, and marketing of these products. The company owns and operates a fleet of 18 vessels, which include single and twin fresh fish trawlers, factory freezer trawlers, and access to in-shore trawlers that catch and process Cape Hake, as well as other by-catch species, such as kingklip and monk. It also has 11 prawn vessels, which catch and process prawns, scallops, crabs, and related by-catch species in Australia. The company distributes various chilled and frozen food products through distribution network; and to local supermarket chains in South Africa, as well as supplies its products to 22 countries, including countries within the European Union, North America, and Australia. It also operates as an agent for Findus, a frozen food brand; and Quorn, a meat-substitute brand, as well as imports and distributes frozen seafood to the catering and hospitality industry. The company was formerly known as Sea Harvest Holdings Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Sea Harvest Group Limited in February 2017. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Sea Harvest Group Limited is a subsidiary of Brimco Proprietary Limited.

Pembury Lifestyle Group Limited provides private education and associated services to preprimary, primary, and high school students. The company operates through PLG Ballito Academy, PLG Hartbeespoort Academy, PLG Mellow Oaks Academy, PLG Northriding Academy, and PLG Willow View Academy segments. Its schools offer pre-primary, primary, and high school education, as well as aftercare services; and operate boarding facilities. The company operates a total of 19 schools on the 7 campuses, which include 7 pre-primary schools, 7 primary schools, and 5 high schools. Pembury Lifestyle Group Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.
